title: peach pie-fresh
directions: Boil sugar, water, and cornstarch until thickened.
Add lemon gelatin (mix with a little water first), butter and coloring. Pour some into baked pie shell.
Slice fresh peaches into it.
Add more mix.
Top with whipped whipping cream.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in oil.
Remove.
In large casserole dish, place 2 chops on bottom, next onion and potatoes, alternating until all is used, keeping 1 or 2 chops for top.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans, water chestnuts, diced potatoes and diced ham in a casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over top and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
About 15 minutes before the end of baking time, add French fried onions and continue baking.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Arrange croutons in baking dish or pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until firm in center.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat the eggs and add milk and crumbs.
Add the corn, seasoning and butter.
Mix together well and pour in a greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Put Minute rice and boiling water into casserole (2 to 3 quart) dish and let stand 15 minutes.
Brown meat, onion and celery.
Place in casserole over rice.
Mix together soy sauce, brown sugar and soup; pour over meat.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lu's blueberry buckle
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Gently fold in berries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add them and vanilla to the mixture.
Mix well.
Place by small balls (about the size of large walnuts) on cookie sheet.
Flatten 2 ways with fork tines.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: taboli salad
directions: Empty wheat into bowl and cover with cold water.
Wheat will expand.
Drain excess water.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix all juices together with sugar and water. Pour over spices in percolator basket and brew at medium temperature.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 3 1/2 cups cold milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or chopped nuts if desired.
Makes 15 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Sift sugar.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Very slowly, add sugar beating constantly.
Fold in vanilla and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° about 25 minutes.
Remove quickly from pan. Makes 4 dozen.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and butter, in this order.
Add scalded milk slowly, stirring constantly to large saucepan.
Cook slowly on medium-low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add 12 ounces coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion for a short time; drain and set aside. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and milk to make sauce. Break up cream cheese; drop into sauce.
Add grated Cheddar cheese, stirring until smooth.
Mix broccoli, onion and sauce in casserole.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter; mix with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Put vegetables in layers and sprinkle with sugar.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle meat with garlic powder.
Place onions on top of meat.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
To serve, slice thinly against the grain.

title: valentine sodas
directions: Fill a tall glass with strawberry ice cream about 3/4 full. Pour ginger ale over the ice cream. Top with whipped cream and strawberry preserves. Serve with a spoon.

title: microwave marshmallow crisp
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish melt butter on High for 1 minute. Add marshmallows and cover.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir; add cereal.
Blend and press firmly into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy funnel cake(just like at the fair!)
directions: Beat together egg and milk.
Combine dry ingredients together. Then gradually add milk and egg to dry ingredients (mix well; there shouldn't be any lumps/bumps)!
Pour into funnel and in a circular motion into saucepan with hot oil.
Load up with powdered sugar and sprinkle when cool!

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix all ingredients (except rum) and bring to a boil, stirring. Remove from heat; cool, stirring once in awhile.
In a cup, add 1 teaspoon mix and shot of rum to boiling water.
Add dash of nutmeg; top with whipped cream.

title: punch
directions: Heat 4 cups water and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved in water.
Add remaining ingredients to sugar/water mixture.
Freeze for at least 24 hours.
Mix with ginger ale when ready to serve. Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans in large mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar, barbecue sauce and catsup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Put raw bacon strips on top of beans and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: geoff's jiffy cake
directions: Empty can of pie filling into 6 x 10-inch buttered Pyrex dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over this just as it comes out of package. Do not pat down.
Melt butter and drizzle it over all.
Sprinkle nuts over the top and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares and serve warm with ice cream.
Tasty last minute dessert.

title: pear honey
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes or longer for a thick syrup.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Beat Ricotta cheese with eggs and parsley flakes.
Mix spinach and sausage into cheese.
Stuff shells and place, open side down, in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with Prego or Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with powdered Parmesan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well for later use.

title: my best "brittle"
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and syrup and microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes (depends on your oven).
Add butter and vanilla; cook for additional 1 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda and mix well. Immediately pour and spread onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Will need a pan and a grown-up assistant with knife.

title: 1-2-3 rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Stir with spoon.
Drop into greased muffin tins and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix until blended.
Fold in sausage.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: bert's beignets(ben'yas)
directions: In large deep iron skillet, heat oil.
While oil is heating, cut biscuits in 1/4 pieces.
Put confectioners sugar in large bowl and set aside.
When oil is heated, drop in biscuit pieces and cook until golden brown.
Immediately take out of oil and roll in the confectioners sugar.
Makes 40 beignets.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, milk, butter and salt. Bring to a full boil.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes with it boiling.
Remove from heat; add chips and stir until melted, then add vanilla and nuts.
Chill 2 hours in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: dream biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients; add milk.
Roll out and cut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs till very foamy.
Fold in cheese, oil, zucchini, soup mix, garlic powder and parsley.
Add Bisquick.
Pour into 9 or 10 inch pie plate, greased with margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 - 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix well; add 1 pound pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan (I use Pam).
Makes approximately 7 pounds.

title: peach pie
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water; add the oil, sugar and salt to the starter.
Add yeast, work in flour.
Add until the dough is of kneading consistency.
Knead well, shape and put in oiled loaf pans.
Oil and put into shape.
Let rise until double. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
You may need to place aluminum foil loosely over the top while baking to keep from burning the top while cooking the inside.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mash avocados with a fork.
Add onion, lemon juice, salt and hot pepper.
Beat until creamy.
Fold in tomato, cover and refrigerate no longer than 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: mott's deliciously quick and easy cake(low-fat and calorie recipe)
directions: Spray desired size pans with cooking spray.

Prepare cake mix according to package directions with the following modifications: Add 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour to the dry mix and stir well. Substitute an equal amount of Mott's natural applesauce for the vegetable oil.
Bake and cool as directed.
Frost cake with your choice of Betty Crocker Creamy Deluxe light frosting and garnish with fresh berries if desired.

title: turkey dressing(mom's)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in frying pan and add onion.
Saute until onion softens (do not brown).
Add butter, onion, salt, pepper and thyme to bread crumbs.
Mix and stuff turkey lightly. Do not press stuffing together.

title: low-fat chocolate sauce
directions: Put sugar in a no-stick skillet and warm.
Pour in the syrup (maple syrup or honey may be used).
Stir and add oil and cocoa. Heat over low heat until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Serve over angel food cake.

title: barbecue beef cups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, sugar and onions to meat mixture.
Separate biscuits and press into muffin pan.
Spoon mixture into biscuit cups and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crunchy cranberry mold
directions: Heat cranberry juice to boiling; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in lemon and orange juices.
Refrigerate until consistency of unbeaten egg white. Fold in relish and nuts.
Spoon into lightly oiled 1-quart mold. Chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter; pour over cookies.
Let ice cream thaw somewhat and spread over cookies and butter.
Pour chocolate fudge on top of ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Oreos on top for looks.

title: fudgy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute; time accurately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Firm in 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole cheese dish
directions: Butter 8 slices of bread.
Sprinkle with cheese (cubed or grated) and the ham.
(Be liberal with the cheese!) Grease pan. Spread sprinkled buttered bread over bottom of pan.
Beat eggs into milk.
Pour over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice according to directions.
Mix rice, Mexicorn and soup and place in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices. Microwave or bake until bubbly.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce and minced onion.
Take biscuits and press each biscuit into an ungreased muffin pan, making sure dough goes up to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: challah bread
directions: Put 4 eggs in mixing bowl; add 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 1/2 cups salad oil and 2 1/2 cups warm water.
Mix lightly.
Add 2 cups flour and 2 packages of dry yeast.
Stir and knead in about 6 cups flour.
Let rise until double.
Divide into thirds.
Divide each third in thirds.
Roll each third into rope on floured surface.
Braid.
Let rise until double in size.
Brush with one egg yolk, beaten with 1 teaspoon water.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg; add milk and lard.
Mix all this well.
Add vinegar last.

title: sweet pepper dressing
directions: Brown meat; add chopped seasonings and cook about 30 minutes. Add tomatoes and continue to cook at least 30 minutes more. Season to taste and mix in hot cooked rice.
Dressing will be moist.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Mix milk, flour, beaten egg whites and vanilla. Fold into butter mix.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Top with cooked sausage and remaining portion of cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard.
Pour this mixture over layered ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half; place 1 half on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets, tie with a string.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This dressing will add an extra taste to just about anything.

title: sheet cake
directions: Use a 9 x 15 jelly roll pan. Prepare cake mix, following directions on box.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil chicken, then shred. Mix first 3 ingredients in a bowl. Add grated cheese. Mix all together. Use only 1 cup of grated cheese. Cut up tortillas. Use a layer of tortillas, then layer of sauce with chicken and layer of cheese. Repeat steps. Bake for 45 minutes; 15 minutes with foil, covering and 30 minutes without foil.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add food coloring.
Add salt and flour. Alternately with vanilla, add milk.
Mix well after each addition. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 10-inch tube pan.

title: green jello salad
directions: Dissolve 2 boxes Jell-O with water.
Add drained can of pineapple. Add cottage cheese and salad dressing.
Put all in blender until cheese is almost smooth.
Chill can of Pet milk for 1 hour in freezer.
Fold in Jell-O and chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine lime juice concentrate, strawberries and 1 pint sherbet.
Blend
until
smooth.
Pour into chilled punch bowl. Add chilled
lemon-lime pop.
Spoon remaining sherbet over the top. Serve.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine pie filling, pineapple, strawberries and mandarin oranges in a large bowl; chill well.
Coat bananas with lemon juice and add to mixture.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Spread in a casserole dish.
Cover with crumbled potato chips. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves a small army.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: Add onions to softened cream cheese. Drain tuna; mash with fork. Combine with cheese, onions, lemon juice, curry powder, mayonnaise and salt. Blend to mix well. Chill before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: low-fat apricot bars
directions: Stir flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cardamon; set aside.
Stir apricot nectar, applesauce and egg until combined.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in dried apricots. Spread in 11 x 7-inch baking pan, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add bananas and flour, salt and soda which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put into 2 small greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot kippered salmon
directions: Place fillets skin side down, side by side, in greased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Drizzle with the liquid smoke.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Drain any liquid.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together, let stand overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Or you can add 1 egg and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: kevin's favorite spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain all grease.
Add sauce and garlic salt.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over cooked spaghetti.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut flowerets.
Chop green onions and add raisins. Crumble the cooked bacon. Add all ingredients together in a bowl.

title: strawberry pineapple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in a gallon container and add pineapple juice and water to fill the container.

title: aunt betty's peanut butter stick cookies
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Cut each slice into 6 sticks.
Toast sticks on a cookie sheet at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Melt in a double boiler 3 heaping tablespoonfuls peanut butter and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Crush 1 package graham crackers and 3 heaping tablespoonfuls powdered sugar.
Dip toasted sticks into melted peanut butter to coat.
Roll in cracker-sugar mixture and cool on wax paper.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Soak brownies in Kahlua.
In a large glass bowl, layer:
1/2 brownies, 1/2 mousse, 1/2 Heath bars and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat.

title: italian dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Shake before serving.

title: depression chili
directions: Saute ground raw rabbit meat in small amount shortening.
Add spices, tomatoes and water.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes on medium heat.
Add flour mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Can be served with homemade cornbread, biscuits or crackers.

title: nutty - noodle clusters
directions: Mix both types of chips in heavy saucepan.
Melt over low heat while stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts.
Mix quickly to coat evenly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.
Makes 24 clusters.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg white and water until frothy. Add nuts; coat well.
Blend spices with sugar; add to nuts. Spread in oiled shallow pan.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
This makes a great Christmas present.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Let cool to lukewarm and combine with remaining ingredients.
Can be molded, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all-purpose flour, baking soda and salt together; stir in whole wheat flour and add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn bread out onto rack.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter to mixture until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Top with milk or ice cream.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix with spoon and beat 1/2 minute. Pour into 8x8x2 pan.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add remainder and mix well. Bake 15 minutes at 375 or 400°.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and lemon. Cook in double boiler until custard thickens, let cool. Add sugar to egg white and beat. Add to the cooled mixture. Fold in whipped cream. Layer 3/4 of the crumb mixture in 1 - 1/2 quart rectangular baking dish. Spread lemon mixture over crumb layer. Sprinkle the remaining crumbs over the lemon mixture. Put in freezer and chill thoroughly. Cut into squares and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrot and onion in small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add sour cream and soup and mix well.
Melt margarine; combine with dressing mix.
Place a layer of dressing mix in bottom of baking dish.
Add squash mixture; top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put in bowl broccoli florets, add 1 diced red onion.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Mix 1 cup Miracle Whip, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon wine vinegar.
Mix and toss over broccoli mixture.

title: venus soup
directions: Saute meat with onion for 10 minutes or until meat is browned. Add remaining ingredients all together, mixing well.
In a deep saucepan on medium heat, stir occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Serves about 6 to 8.
Season to taste.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Layer potatoes and onion rings in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Add bread crumbs to middle layer.
Mix soup with milk and pour over potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a medium bowl, blend corn meal, baking powder and flour. Stir in water, egg and 1 cup cheese.
Spread 1/2 of the corn meal mixture in a 9-inch greased pie plate. Set aside.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight.
Add tomatoes just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream (maw-maw's)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk.
Pour into ice cream maker and fill to the fill line with regular whole milk.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased pan and bake.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Grind up the potato chips into powder or small pieces.
Take the chicken after it has been washed and dip into butter and eggs. Roll the chicken in the potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and eggs one at a time. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture alternately with coffee. Fold in diced apples and chopped walnuts. Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over top. Bake in a 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes. Test for doneness.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in bowl and set aside.
Combine margarine, cocoa and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
See Chocolate Icing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan. Add soups and mushrooms. Stir until well blended. Remove from heat. Add pimento, chicken, spaghetti and sour cream. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 alarm chili
directions: Brown hamburg; drain fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Let simmer for 45 minutes.
May add can of pinto beans, fresh tomato, green pepper and chopped onion the last 5 minutes of cooking. Garnish with shredded lettuce and shredded cheese (Monterey Jack or Cheddar).

title: hot bean and cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients plus 1/4 cup water in saucepan. Stir constantly until heated through.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: ham chowder
directions: Combine water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Microwave on Full power 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not drain! Melt margarine in microwave dish.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk.
Microwave on Full power 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until thick.
Add cheese to milk/flour to make cheese sauce.
Add cheese sauce, corn and ham to vegetables.
Heat on Full power 3 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Do not boil.
Serve hot with bread and crackers.

title: caramel nut brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, melted oleo, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 2 tablespoons water.
Pour or pat 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and blend in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and blend in butter and vanilla.

title: chocolate chip bran cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll in small balls (kids can help with this job).
Then roll in powdered sugar twice.
That's it!
Store in tight covered container.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Cut in the peanut butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Set aside 2 teaspoons for garnish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs into a pie shell.
Combine 2/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup cornstarch, egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Remove from the heat; add butter and vanilla, stirring until butter melts.
Pour into pie shell.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Mix the jello as directed on box less 1/2 cup water.
Add strawberries.
Let cool.
Add the bananas.
Pour into greased mold or dish. Top with the sour cream with the sugar mixed in.

title: german chocolate cake frosting
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks and shortening. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture come to a boil. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, coconut and pecans. Beat until thick. Cool 15 minutes and then spread on your cake.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add shortening to dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients.
Roll between two sheets of wax paper.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is as fine as cornmeal.
Add liquid and mix very lightly until a soft dough is formed.
Drop from teaspoon on boiling meat stew.
Cover very tightly and cook without removing cover 12 minutes.
Serves 6.
Keep covered while cooking to prevent sogginess.
Richer dumplings may be made by using 1 beaten egg and 1/4 cup milk, instead of 1/2 cup milk.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter until soft.
Sift together brown sugar and white sugar.
Add sugar gradually to butter and blend until creamy.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt and soda. Add sifted flour to batter.
Blend in vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with fork.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chorice appetizers
directions: Slice sausage thin diagonally.
Slice bacon in half.
On one slice of bacon, place sausage and date.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Bake for 20 minutes.
May be turned after 10 minutes. Broil for 1 or 2 minutes on each side.

title: cinnamon rolls(bread machine)
directions: Put ingredients (yeast, 1/2 cup melted butter, 1/2 cup warm water, 2/3 cup warm milk, bread flour, wheat flour, eggs and 3 tablespoons of sugar) in order required by your machine.
Put on dough cycle.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Cook the 1 cup raisins and 1 cup water together until about 5 tablespoons of water remains.
Drain and reserve the liquid.
Mix together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the cooled raisin liquid and the vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together and stir into the dough.
Stir in the cooked raisins and the rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ranch style snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour crackers into paper bag.
Add oil mixture and shake, shake, shake until crackers are coated.
Store in airtight plastic container at room temperature.

title: chili rice
directions: Stir chili, tomatoes, onion, garlic powder and pepper in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: ham pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss macaroni with ham, green pepper, tomato and onion.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, milk and salt.
Pour over pasta mixture and stir to coat.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook chicken; skin and debone.
Pull apart in chunks.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add soup, milk, flour and salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Cook wild rice as directed on box.
In baking dish, put 1 layer of rice and 1 layer of chicken, then add sauce.
(May make 2 layers.) Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese.

title: hashed brown rice
directions: Combine the rice, flour and milk. Heat butter in a 10-inch skillet. Add onions and cook until tender. Spread the rice mixture evenly in the skillet. Press it down firmly with a spatula. Cook over medium heat until bottom is golden brown. Turn out onto serving dish, brown side up. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in gently, the buttermilk.
Knead for 2 minutes.
Pat the dough to thickness of 1/4 inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Lightly season chicken and dredge in flour.
Brown in frying pan.
When brown, put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Pour over chicken and bake an additional 10 minutes.
For 10 pieces or more, double the recipe.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In greased baking pan, place chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken; top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice and chicken risotto(risotto, my dear, is a way with rice; a delectable way.)
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Place in a large baking dish. Cover and cook in the oven at 400° until liquid is absorbed. (More liquid may be added for tender rice.)
Remove cover the last 15 minutes to lightly brown.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly.
Add eggs, flour and salt. Blend well.
Add vanilla; mix, then chill.
Roll out on dough board and cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot rotel dip
directions: Saute pepper and onion in two tablespoons oleo or cooking oil.
Add sausage and continue to stir until sausage is browned. Drain on paper towels.
In crock pot, place cubed cheese and drained Rotel tomatoes.
Add sausage mixture, olives, pimentos, and Italian seasoning.
Continue to stir until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly combined.
Serve from crockpot with tortilla chips.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Shred or chop beef into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together 2 hours prior to serving.
Serve with crackers or rye rounds.

title: kitchen sink cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir well.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well and add vanilla, oats, cornflakes, chocolate chips and nuts.
Make balls and flatten with a fork dipped in ice water.
Bake at 375° for about 13 minutes.

title: liberty bell steak sandwiches
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Remove onions from skillet.
Add meat to skillet.
Heat thoroughly.
Heat process cheese spread in saucepan over low heat.
Fill roll with meat and onions.
Top with process cheese spread.

title: glazed fresh carrots
directions: Cook carrots (covered with water) on stove over low heat until tender. Drain carrots and cover with butter and brown sugar.

title: southwestern muffins
directions: Saute peppers and onion in 2 tablespoons oil until tender; stir in ham.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; make well in center.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry mixture with the peppers and ham.
Mix until just moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice the lemons into paper-thin rounds, rind and all.
Place slices in a bowl.
Pour sugar over and mix gently.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Prepare pie crust and chill until ready for use.
Heat oven to 450°.
Beat the eggs, pour over lemons and mix gently. Pour lemon mixture into pie shell.
Cover pie with top crust, which may be gashed decoratively to let steam escape.
Bake 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes more. Pie is done if a knife inserted into it comes out clean.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Add ground beef and lightly brown.
Do not overcook.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on a bed of rice.
Makes a meal with green salad and French bread.

title: divinity
directions: Make divinity by combining sugar, syrup and hot water.
Cook until the mixture spins a thread (when thread spins from almost empty spoon).
Pour cooked syrup into 3 beaten egg whites.
Mix until peaks for candy stand up when dropped from a spoon.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins. Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until set.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.
Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: cinnamon blossoms
directions: Separate biscuits with scissors.
Make 5 cuts at regular intervals, almost to center of each biscuit.
Drop biscuits into hot oil in fryer.
Fry 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.
Drain.
Coat warm blossoms with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Margarine and cheese should be room temperature.
Cream.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Use several dashes of Tabasco.
Add Rice Krispies, mix.
Make into marble size balls.
Press with fork until flat.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 250.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives.
Combine water and vinegar with egg; add to flour mixture and stir until moistened and dough is formed. Divide dough into 4 or 5 equal parts; shape each into a round flat patty ready for rolling.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill at least 30 minutes.
Place on lightly floured board; roll 1/8-inch thick and 2 inches larger than inverted pie pan.

title: crispy pork chops
directions: Cut off excess fat from edges of chops.
Bread chops in the egg and crumbs, coating well.
Broil on a lightly greased rack about 8 inches away from heat for 10 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Do not cook!
Melt butter.
Let cool, then add powdered sugar, coconut, Eagle Brand milk and nuts. Roll into balls.
Dip in chocolate mixture.
Let set on wax paper.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix the remaining ingredients together, mixing the third cup by hand.
Set in a bowl in warm water with damp towel over top for 15 minutes.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.

title: brenda's spice tea
directions: Mix and store.
Add 3 tablespoons to cup of hot water. Absolutely delicious!

title: meat and macaroni dish
directions: Fry meat in fat until lightly browned with onions, salt and pepper. Have macaroni cooked and drained. In a well oiled baking dish, put layer of meat on bottom, then layer of macaroni, then top with layer of meat mixture. Cover with can of tomato soup. Dot with butter and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add enough all-purpose flour until cutting consistency.
This usually takes about 3 cups.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
The thinner you roll them, the crispier.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Place in large saucepan.
Cover with water. Add salt.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove chicken; cool and take meat from bones.
Cut into chunks.
Save broth. Melt butter in 3-quart pan.
Add flour and mix.
Add broth; cook until thick.
Add soup and stir until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper, if needed.
Serve over cooked rice or chow mein noodles.

title: beanie weenie salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
In large bowl cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Add beans, chopped pickles, onions and eggs.
Toss with your favorite salad dressing.

title: beef cream cheese ball
directions: Allow the two packages of cream cheese to soften.
Slice the beef into small pieces and place about 1/4 to the side.
Food processor is ideal for slicing.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream 1/2 cup margarine.
Add sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and flour.
Press evenly into tiny tart shells or muffin cups.
Use paper liners.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
(Adjust ingredients quantities to individual taste.)
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Cover and bake for an additional 15 minutes baking time.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine green tomatoes, red peppers, onion and hot pepper in large saucepan.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into hot sterilized pint jars.
Seal with two-piece lids.
Hot water bath 5 to 7 minutes.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat in large casserole dish; drain grease.
Add potato rounds, then Ranch Style beans, then tomatoes and about 1/2 can of water.
Spread chunks of cheese around on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Mix sugar and cream cheese, then add to jello.
Let set, then add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and 3/4 stick margarine together and mix into vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch oven dish.
Roll crackers crumbs and mix with 1/4 stick margarine.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Add Eagle Brand milk. Add vanilla wafers and bananas. Chill for 2 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple and add juice to cake mix for the liquid; mix according to directions.
In large casserole dish or large pan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Stir until sugar is well wet. Layer pineapple.
Add nuts and cherries, then pour on cake mix. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until cake springs back.
Turn upside-down on cake plate and lift slowly.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls into lightly greased 12 inch pizza pan.
Firmly press lines to seal.
Combine eggs, bacon, cheese and mushrooms. Pour over prepared crust and bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Chill.

title: our favorite pizza
directions: Thaw pastry sheet and fold open. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Place tomato slices on waxed paper and sprinkle evenly with salt. Let stand 20 minutes. Sprinkle baked pastry shell with Mozzarella cheese and Feta cheese. Arrange tomato slices in a single layer to cover top. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and olive oil. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage, uncooked, into casserole dish.
Top with rice and cooked ground beef.
Pour soup and water mixture next.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven (turn oven off) until cheese is melted.
Cover tightly with foil while cooking.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half the potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with half the onions.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and milk and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix hot water and Kool-Aid and let cool.
Mix bananas with sugar.
Add pineapple mixture.
Let set overnight in freezer. Punch is best when served while slushy.

title: sugar-free fruity thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine the flour, egg, butter, artificial sweetener, coconut flavoring and apple juice.
Beat until smooth.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a foil-lined baking sheet, spacing the cookies about 2 inches apart.

title: granny's sunday dinner chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Mix buttermilk and eggs together. Wash chicken and drain. Sprinkle with flour. Dip chicken in buttermilk mix. Fork chicken 1 piece at a time and drop in flour mixture. Take out and drop in hot oil just until chicken is brown. Take out and put single layer on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes. It's good enough for the preacher!

title: low calorie dip
directions: Blend to sour cream consistency.
Use as a dip with cauliflowerets, cucumber slices, celery and carrot sticks and other vegetables.
Contains 210 calories per cup.

title: foundation or plain cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the shortening; add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch layers. Frost as desired.
Good with Chocolate Frosting.

title: molded spinach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water in large bowl and let cool. Stir in lemon juice and salt. Cover and chill in refrigerator until partially set.

title: best slaw
directions: Heat the sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Pour over the cabbage and onions.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours in an airtight container.
Drain to serve.
Will keep for 2 weeks refrigerated.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Combine oatmeal and Parmesan cheese in blender and blend until oatmeal is fine.
Skin chicken, if desired, and brush with barbecue sauce.
Coat chicken with oatmeal mixture, shaking off excess.
Place, skin side down, in lightly greased baking pan.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread cream cheese on heat resistant dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Spread salsa over chili.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Microwave until Cheddar is melted or put in 350° oven until Cheddar melts.
Serve with nachos or corn chips.

title: play dough
directions: Add food color to water.
Mix all together.
Stir over low heat until mixture foams, forms into ball and clings to spoon.

title: tom's famous meat loaf
directions: Mix together; can add more minute oats if needed for a soft but not firm consistency.
Put in loaf pan or 9 x 13 pan and shape into a loaf.

title: two cheesy biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, cut Crisco into flour, until Crisco is the texture of peas.
Add milk and mix.
The dough should be wet.
Add grated cheese.
Mix.
Dump onto floured surface.
Knead four times.
Roll or pat out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Using a biscuit cutter or a glass, cut biscuits. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sour cream, Ranch dressing and dill.
Then add vegetables.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat. Heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows and chips melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Separate egg whites and beat until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add egg yolks one at a time, then flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add flavoring. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool ten minutes, take out of pan and add glaze.

title: dirt
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Oreos, together.
Crumble Oreos. Layer in a deep dish the cookies and cream mixture, ending with cookies on top.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel and chop oranges.
Add coconut and sugar to taste. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Wash, remove stem
ends and cores and quarter tomatoes. Let tomatoes stand in colander to drain off excess liquid.
In 8 to 10 quart kettle, combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil;
cook 30
to
minutes,
stirring occasionally.
Put tomato
mixture through strainer.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt to
tomato
puree. Return
to
kettle.
Bring
to
a boil and simmer
until
desired consistency, about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Pour
hot tomato sauce into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch space
and
seal
(boiling water bath - 10 minutes).
Makes 2 pints.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add soup, sauce, water and olives.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour Doritos into large casserole dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over Doritos.
Mix slightly.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven 15 minutes at 400°.

title: wyoming squares
directions: Beat the whites of 7 eggs until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until mixture is very stiff.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar still beating.
Beat the egg yolks until thick and add lemon flavoring.
Then fold them into the egg whites very gently.
Add 1 cup of cake flour; sift before measuring.
Flavor with orange extract, almond extract and vanilla.
Bake in square or oblong pan from 30 to 40 minutes.
When cake has risen, the heat may be reduced slightly.
When cool, cake may be cut into squares; cover each square with a butter icing.
Coconut could be sprinkled over this.

title: gingerbread dancers a la cynthia gregory
directions: Cream the softened butter with brown sugar and add molasses. Mix dry ingredients and add to the butter/sugar mixture with water to form a soft ball.

title: christmas lizzies
directions: Chop fruit and pecans.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in small cupcake pans for 15 or 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple delish
directions: Drain pineapple saving juice.
Prepare cake mix according to directions, substituting pineapple juice for liquid.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan for about 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool Cake.
Whip together cream cheese, pudding and milk until smooth.
Spread over cooled cake top.
With drained pineapple, cover with Cool Whip. Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter; add confectioners sugar and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Chill well.
Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip the balls into the melted chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Store in a cool place.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Stir in apples.
May also use zucchini, walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in paper cupcake holders 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle over noodles 2 tablespoons caraway seed.
Crumble corned beef over noodles.
Spread sauerkraut over meat.
Mix cheese soup with milk and pour over.
Spread Swiss cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: In saucepan, combine frozen vegetables and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain the ground beef and onion. Add the spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and water. Cook this slowly. Spread in the bottom of a Pyrex dish. Layer on top the Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and dinner rolls. Dot with butter. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: angel cake custard
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook in top of double boiler until coats spoon. Add vanilla.
Add gelatin which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Cool.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Stir in pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar. Place in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, stirring once or twice. Remove and cool.

title: creamy orange cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons butter; press onto bottom of a spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each one. Blend in milk, vanilla and rind.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: furniture polish
directions: Mix all together.
Recipe from 1904 Gold Medal Cookbook.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Top with crumble pie topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; may cover to keep the top from browning too fast.

title: banana bread
directions: Soften margarine.
Mash bananas with fork.
Sift flour with baking soda.
Combine all ingredients; add chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured loaf pan.

title: mushroom patties
directions: Mix ingredients into a batter.
Pour about 1/4 inch or more oil in a skillet.
When oil is hot, take a tablespoon of batter at a time, and place in hot oil.
Flip once and fry until golden brown.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Soak soft bread crumbs in scalded milk.
Add salt, dry mustard and cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Let cool as you clean salmon; remove skin and bones.
Add egg yolks.
Fold in 2 cups flaked salmon (1 pound).
Fold in 3 egg whites, beaten stiff.

title: wacky kake
directions: Into one 8-inch cake pan (ungreased), sift the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
With the back end of a spoon, make a hole in the dry ingredients and add the oil.
Make another hole and add the vinegar.
Make another hole and add vanilla.
Pour the water over all the ingredients and now mix well with a fork. Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as directed, simmering 15 minutes. Remove from skillet; set aside.
Keep warm.
In same skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add green onions, garlic and ginger; cook 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and prepared Rice-A-Roni.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add pea pods.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until crisp-tender.

title: forty cloves of garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large Dutch oven, melt butter in olive oil.
Add chicken and cook, turning until golden, 5 to 10 minutes.
Tilt pan and spoon off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add garlic and stir to coat.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, thyme, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup water.
Cover tightly and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Using 1 stick of margarine, coat the sides and bottom of the crock-pot.
Place half of the potatoes into the crock-pot.
Add 1/4 cup onions, 1/2 stick of margarine and 1 can of Cheddar cheese soup.
Add remaining potatoes, onion, margarine, butter and Cheddar cheese soup.
Add cream of potato soup last.
Place lid on crock-pot and cook for 6 to 8 hours.

title: susan's wine stew
directions: Brown meat in oil; add onions, garlic, juice, wine and seasonings.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Stir in mushrooms and bouillon.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss the ingredients together; cover with grated cheese and a few crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: italian marinade for steak or venison
directions: Score meat in crisscross pattern 1 inch apart and 1/4 inch deep.
Marinate in glass container 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal into (salted) boiling water.
Stir for 1 minute and remove from the fire.
Add butter; beat well.
Add eggs and beat in the cold milk.
Beat again and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes in hot oven (450°).
Serve from baking dish.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Add milk to beaten egg yolks.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, flour and butter.
Add rest of ingredients except the egg whites. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set casserole in pan of hot water in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, uncovered.
It will be slightly brown on top.
Cake will be on top and pudding on the bottom.
Include a little of each in each serving.
Make it morning it is to be served.
Serve at room temperature or cold with a whipped cream, if you like.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and onion (optional) and simmer while noodles cook.
Cook noodles with salt and vegetable oil according to package directions and drain. Layer 1/2 noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Layer crushed Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Layer each ingredient in order as given on top of Oreos. Top with remaining Oreos.
Keep in freezer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with more cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: triple chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in mixer and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half of batter into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Sprinkle 1 cup morsels over batter.
Spoon remaining batter over morsels.
Sprinkle with 1 cup morsels and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 35 minutes; invert on a serving platter and cool completely.
Combine remaining morsels and cream in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring, until morsels are melted.
Cool 15 minutes.
Pour glaze over cake, using a frosting spatula to coat sides.
Top with pecan halves.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix together crackers and melted margarine.
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Put remainder on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat with mixer until smooth ice cream, pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cracker crumbs that you pressed down.
Chill 2 hours or make day before.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip and sprinkle with remainder crumbs on top.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, tear bread. In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly. Pour over bread and add more bread as needed to absorb mixture. Bake 65 to 70 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pineapple-lemon chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary. Arrange chicken in shallow casserole dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt.
Broil until browned.
Stir sauce.
Pour over chicken. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Arrange pineapple and lemon around chicken.
Spoon sauce over all.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings with only 229 calories per serving.

title: tropical fruit 'n nut bars
directions: Drain pineapple well, pressing out juice (1 1/2 cups) in saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over reserved juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in honey, pineapple and other ingredients.
Turn into 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: super easy braided bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil and salt.
Add three cups flour; mix well.
Add enough flour to make a nice soft dough. Knead 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Divide in 3 parts.
Roll out in strands, 10 x 14-inches long.
Braid and place on sheet either straight or crescent shaped.
Let rise to double.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: cranberry apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine the cranberries, apples, sugar, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour.
Transfer the mixture to a greased 6-cup shallow baking dish.
In same bowl (no need to wash it), combine the remaining flour, brown sugar, oats and nuts, if desired.
Stir in the melted butter.
Mix the ingredients well (should be crumbly).
Sprinkle the oat mixture over the fruit mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until the crisp is lightly brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Serves 12.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in just enough water to cover until tender. Do not rinse.
Add milk, pepper and potato flakes.
Simmer until thickened.
(May use more instant potato flakes if you prefer a thicker soup.)
You may also add diced ham, canned salmon or bacon to this soup.
Garnish with shredded cheese prior to serving.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper, making a paste.
Add chicken broth and light cream slowly so it doesn't get lumpy.
Add rest of ingredients and heat slowly, stirring well.
Serve in prepared patty shells.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.

title: kathryn's almost fried fish
directions: Dip fish in vinegar or soak if time permits.
Mix together corn meal, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper.
Coat fish after vinegar with corn meal mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle leftover mixture on top.
Pour melted margarine over top and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Do not turn.
Yields 2 servings

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.
Excellent frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: french salad dressing
directions: In blender, grate onion, garlic and vinegar.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in fridge.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until all melted.
May add milk as needed for desired thickness.
Pour cheese mixture over chips and add desired topping to your taste.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Melt in large saucepan: margarine and brown sugar.
Beat eggs and add to butter mixture.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken livers and potatoes
directions: Clean and butter outside of potatoes. Wrap in aluminum and put in oven at 400°. Pour 1/4 cup of oil in frying pan.
Clean and drain livers on paper towel. Add 1 cup flour, salt and pepper into a large bowl.
Put livers into flour mixture.
Place in hot frying pan. Turn until done. When chicken livers are done, take rest of flour mix and put in frying pan.
Constantly stir until medium brown.
Pour in water and onion and simmer. After potatoes are done, slice open and pour livers and gravy mixture onto the split baked potato.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine sherry, soy sauce, oil, ketchup, pepper, pepper sauce, ginger and garlic and mix thoroughly for marinade.
Pour marinade over chicken halves and let marinate overnight.
Cook on open grill or in the oven until fork-tender.

title: green tomato pickle *
directions: Cut tomatoes and onions in small pieces.
Combine peppers, vinegar, sugar, tomatoes and onions in open kettle.
Add sugar and salt.
Boil at low temperature about 4 hours.

title: chipped beef chicken
directions: Mix soup and sour cream and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Wrap each chicken breast in chipped beef and "bury" it in soup mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake uncovered for 3 hours at 275°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs. Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the sides of the bowl. Turn out onto slightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out dough into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over and spread fruit evenly over the dough. Roll up like a jelly roll. Dampen the edge of dough with a little water to seal.
Slice lengthwise into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a pan with melted butter.
Pour the sugar syrup carefully around the rolls.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rouladen(beef rolls)
directions: Pound meat until thin and nearly double in size. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown bacon and onions in small skillet, then crumble. Place small amount of mustard on one side of meat; top with spoonful of bacon and onions. Roll up meat slices and tie with string or secure with toothpicks. Lightly coat with flour each roll of meat.

Brown each roll in skillet, turning until brown. Drain excess oil from skillet; add water, bouillon and tomato sauce. Add water to cover meat rolls. Cook 1 hour until meat is tender. Serve over noodles.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place a slice of lemon on each chop.
Sprinkle brown sugar on chops.
Mix catsup and water; pour around chops until they are just covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until well done.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat with a spoon until smooth and fluffy.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove.
Pour off half the fat.
In remaining fat, cook onion and green pepper until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, water, long grain rice, chili sauce, salt, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.
Trim with parsley.
Makes about 5 to 6 servings.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: The catfish should be in the 8 to 10-inch range, but chunks cut from bigger fish are commonly used.
The best fat for deep frying is a mixture of two parts bacon drippings to one part lard.
Heat the fat in a big, deep kettle until it will brown a 1-inch cube of bread in 40 seconds.
Mix salt and pepper with corn meal; roll the fish in it.
Toss them into the kettle, a few at a time, so temperature of the fat will not be lowered abruptly.
Three to four minutes cooks the fish thoroughly and browns the outside crisply.
Drain on a stack of papers before serving.
Have a crock of dill or sour pickles handy.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding cream of tartar, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Fold in other ingredients and drop on very lightly greased cookie sheet, by teaspoonfuls. Put in oven and let bake for 5 minutes and turn off the oven.
Let them sit in oven for about 3 hours, or until you are ready to take them out.
Hence, the name, Forgotten.

title: chicken nugget batter
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl or bag and shake to mix. Add chicken and shake until battered. Remove excess batter and deep-fry at 350° until golden brown.

title: grilled portabella bruschetta
directions: 1. Clean off mushrooms and remove the gills. Place on a plate and drizzle with 2 tablespoons of olive oil and vinegar.
Let stand for 30-60 minutes.
Meanwhile, start the grill to med-high.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, Karo, salt and nuts.
Place in an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 420° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.
Test with a knife until clean.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Combine sesame oil and five-spice powder in a skillet and heat to medium-high heat; add beef and brown. Remove from pan.

title: hot chocolate drink mix
directions: Stir until blended.
Store in tight container.
For hot chocolate, use water just below boiling point.
Amount used may be varied to suit individual tastes.
About 3 tablespoons.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Make into balls and roll into sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes.

title: pita sandwich
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stuff into pita halves.

title: mama alicia's salad dressing
directions: Place equal amounts of vegetable oil and lime juice in a small shallow bowl.
Add sliced onions and very thin slices of radishes. Sprinkle with salt to taste.
As this dressing sits, it will take on the radishes' pink color.
Serve with a spoon over salad greens.

title: duff's bread pudding
directions: Blend together water and powdered milk.
Add eggs.
Blend salt, vanilla and sugar together.
Mix well with first mixture.
Add raisins and melted margarine to mixture.
Mix torn bread into liquid mixture until lightly moistened.
(Don't overmix.)
Bake at 350° in a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan until light brown.
Test by sticking a toothpick in center.
If it comes out clean, pudding is done.
Top with Bread Pudding Sauce.

title: choplet parmesan
directions: Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Dip choplets in bread crumbs and fry.
Put a small amount of sauce in bottom of baking dish. Layer choplets, cheese and sauce alternately in that order, reserving a small amount of cheese for top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Goes well with creamed potatoes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over chicken in pan.
Bake, covered, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
May want to remove cover for a while to reduce sauce.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons butter and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add egg and mix until well blended.
Press into pan.
Pour pie filling over crust.
Spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons butter, nuts and brown sugar.
Beat until mixed.
Sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar and molasses until hard ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat; beat in 1 teaspoon soda and pour over popcorn. Shape into balls; dampen hands a little as needed.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix and stir well together.
Bake at 350°.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, garlic and salt in a large zip-top plastic bag, shaking well to combine.
Combine lemon juice and oil. Brush over both sides of chicken.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, in the bag, shaking to coat.
Remove chicken from bag and place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: low-fat blueberry cake
directions: In large mixer bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, applesauce, milk and egg whites.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange blueberries on top.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Shape
into
strawberries
and roll in red sugar candy. Dip top in green sugar for leaves.

title: cherry cheese cake milk brownies
directions: Brownie Crust:
Stir together the brownie mix, butter and chopped pecans to form a crumb mixture.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Put remaining mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to form crust. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, salt, pepper and egg in a bowl and form into small balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Put in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Slice 4 or 5 potatoes over the meat.
Heat 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of milk until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and meat. Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°, until potatoes are done.

title: fried corn bread
directions: Mix baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Then add buttermilk and egg.
Stir in cornmeal until batter is like thick pancake batter.
Add one tablespoon of melted grease or cooking oil.
Fry in hot skillet.

title: beer batter for shrimp
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs; add beer and half and half.
Add flour and mix well.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature before using.
Dip shrimp in batter; fry in Crisco until a golden color.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Combine lemon jello, boiling water, pineapple juice and vinegar.
Let thicken a bit and add celery, pineapple and cranberry.
Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Arrange tortilla chips in and up sides of large casserole dish. Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into casserole dish and cover with grated cheese. Bake 1 hour in 300° to 350° oven.

title: italian soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a rapid boil.
Beat the eggs with the cheese and parsley.
Pour slowly into the boiling soup, stirring with a fork until egg mixture separates into little shreds. Remove from heat immediately to avoid toughening the eggs.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately with additional grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sweet apple butter
directions: Cook apples in water in large saucepan until very tender. Press through food mill and measure 4 quarts applesauce.
Bring to boil in large saucepan.
Add sugar, cinnamon candies and cinnamon. Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly to dissolve sugar and candies.
Stir in Sure-Jell.
Cook for 10 minutes or until of desired consistency, stirring constantly.
Spoon into 16 hot sterilized half pint jars. leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with 2-piece lids.
Yield:
16 half-pint jars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, 1/4 cup melted margarine, onion flakes and grated cheese.
Pour over the hash browns that have been thawed in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with 1/2 stick melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruited cheese salad
directions: Beat cottage cheese well.
Add dry jello and beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip and drained crushed pineapple.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve topped with a cherry.

title: italian delight
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground round steak, chopped onions and clove of garlic in olive oil.
After browning meat, add the corn, tomatoes, tomato soup and mushrooms.
Stir to blend well.
Mix cooked ingredients and noodles in a greased (I use Pam) casserole dish.
Top mixture with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 8.
Don't forget the green salad and garlic bread.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Combine zucchini, green pepper, celery, onion and pimiento in a medium bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables; toss gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight. Serve with a slotted spoon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated italian chicken
directions: Prepare 1 cruet of Good Seasons dressing; mix in 1 clove of garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
May be grilled or baked until done, usually 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, salt, pepper, garlic powder, sugar, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Stir sauce.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles as directed on package.

title: poor boy's strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease lightly and flour 2 (8 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cut shortening into pancake mix until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs, 1 carton of yogurt, brown sugar and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Turn mixture into prepared pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.

title: carolyn's marinade(for beef, chicken or ribs)
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate your favorite meats!

title: oriental chicken
directions: Dip chicken in mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt-free lemon pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, nuts and melted butter (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: persimmon pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add the sifted dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Fold in the persimmon, milk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased mold.
Place in a pan of water. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, in cup, stir together cornstarch and 1/4 cup water until smooth.
In same skillet, combine 3/4 cup water, onion soup mix and sugar.
Add apples, stirring to coat.
Heat to boiling.
Return chops to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until chops are no longer pink.
Remove chops and apples to serving platter.
Keep warm.
Over medium heat, heat sauce to boiling. Gradually stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Spoon over pork chops and apples.

title: southern squash casserole
directions: Layer in large casserole dish, 1/2 squash, 1/2 stuffing, 1/2 soup, 1/2 sour cream and 1/2 spices and onion; repeat.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 4.

title: tuna croquettes with hash brown patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide evenly into 4 well-greased custard cups.
Place cups on rack and add the frozen hash brown potato patties.
Spread with margarine.
Bake at 375° until well browned.

title: make day before chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Bake 1 hour or until set at 350°.
Cover part of the time baked. Serves 8.

title: bowzer bones(a treat for your dog)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, oatmeal, bacon crumbles and seasonings.
Add eggs and gradually add broth until mixture is just moist enough to shape into a ball.
(If too moist, add a little more flour.
If too dry, add more broth).
Generously flour work surface. Roll out mixture to a thickness of 1/4-inch. Dip edges of cookie cutter into vegetable oil and cut out shapes.
Use a doggie bone cutter if available.
They can sometimes be found in cookware shops.
Place Bowzer Bones on microwave cookie sheet in a single layer, do not crowd.
Cook on High power for 8 to 10 minutes or until firm.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.
Makes 1 dozen bones.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Mix sugar, milk, 1 stick butter, eggs and vanilla with the potatoes.
Pour the mixture into a baking dish.
Melt together brown sugar, 3/4 stick butter, pecans and marshmallows.
Pour over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45-60min., until bubbly and caramel looking on top.

title: toffee
directions: Cook in heavy sauce pan or skillet to cracking stage the brown sugar and butter stirring often to keep from scorching.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 7-Up.
Bake at 350° until springs back to touch, about 30 minutes.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt to beaten egg yolks and cook in top of double boiler until custard consistency.
Pour cold water in bowl and sprinkle gelatin on top of water.
Add to hot custard and stir until dissolved.
Add grated lemon rind, cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which the other 1/2 cup sugar has been added.
Fill baked pie shell; serve with whipped cream.

title: honey carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the carrot liquid.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix dry jello and thawed berries until dissolved.
Add Cool Whip and blend together.
Put in a large bowl; chill before serving.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: *Fifteen varieties in one bag.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Measure corn syrup and sugar into large 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add rice cereal.
Stir until well coated. Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour ingredients into blender and blend.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab mold
directions: Mix together soup and cream cheese in saucepan on low. Dissolve gelatine in water and add to soup mixture and reheat. Don't boil.
Add celery, green pepper, onion, shrimp, crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Pour in a large ring mold and chill 6 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips on a large baking sheet.
Top each with beans and a few green chilies.
Sprinkle each with a tablespoon of cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: sunshine breakfast muffins
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients in food processor until fine. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into baking cups in muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: basic pudding mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in covered container. Prepare as directed in individual recipe.
Makes 24 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and chop spinach; drain and chop water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients.
Tear out center of bread into mouth-size pieces to make bowl for dip.
Put dip in center of bread and use pieces of bread you tore out to dip in the dip.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese well.
Add milk and pudding.
Cover with Dream Whip and nuts.

title: easy rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
