Mix well. Cover and refrigerate (dough will keep a few days).
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins until half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Grease 11 x 17 dish.
Place chicken on bottom, broccoli on top.
Combine soup, lemon juice, curry powder, and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with mixture of cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 package of jello and 3 to 4 drops of red food coloring.
Add the pint of strawberries.
Pour into freshly baked crust.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whip cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together well and bake in 2-quart dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add shortening and boiling water.
Allow this mixture to stand for 15 minutes.
Stir to blend.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs slightly and add vanilla.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Add to date mixture.
Do not overmix.
Place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° (moderate) oven.
When done, toothpick inserted in the center will come out clean.
Cool before removing.
Loosen sides with a spatula.
For perfect slicing, allow the loaf to cool several hours.

title: 7 layer fiesta dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and seasoning mix.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Layer guacamole, salsa, lettuce, cheese, onions and olives over cream cheese mixture.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate any remaining dip.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients over low heat until bubbling and not lumpy.
Pour hot mixture over the sugar and flour.
Add the beaten eggs, milk, soda and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: toll house cookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to
375°.	Combine
in
bowl
the vanilla, margarine and salt.
Blend	well.
Gradually
beat	in
sugar. Add flour and
chocolate bits.	Press evenly onto ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press into the dough. Bake for 25 minutes in a 375° oven.	Watch until golden brown. Cool.
Drain on paper towels and break into brittle.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine sausage and ground beef.
Mix well.
Add about 1/5 of the spices and flavoring, 1/2 cup red wine and 1 tablespoon olive oil. Cook until brown. Add to sauce.

title: chocolate marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the remaining ingredients; beat well. Bake in large cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with miniature marshmallows.
Bake until they are nicely puffed up.
Frost while still warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add rest of the ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until a silver knife inserted 1-inch from side comes out clean.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients, except walnuts; top with walnuts. Put in casserole or baking dish.
Heat in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: golden raisin salad dressing
directions: In pan mix vinegar and sugar.
Stir and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add dried onion.
With mixer or whisk, add oils.
Add salt, mustard and celery seed; mix well.
Pour over salad.

title: raisin no knead batter bread
directions: Insert dough hooks into mixer.
Scald milk; add butter and cool to room temperature.
Pour warm water into large mixing bowl; add yeast and dissolve thoroughly.
Place milk mixture, sugar, salt, raisins and 3 cups flour into mixer bowl.
Turn mixer to speed #3 to moisten ingredients, about 1/2 minute Turn mixer to speed #7 and mix thoroughly, about 3 minutes.
Gradually add 2 cups flour (reserve 1/4 cup flour for board and hands).
Total mixing time should not exceed 8 minutes.
Let dough rise in bowl for 30 minutes.
Turn dough out onto heavily floured board; flour hands and divide dough in half.
Form loaves.
Place in two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Baked loaf will sound hollow when tapped with knuckles.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until center is puffed.
Cool.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
One-half cup of flaked coconut may also be added if desired.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour soup and milk into a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Place biscuits over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain; add butter and mash.
Mix sugar, egg, mayonnaise, nuts, pepper, onion, salt and cheese.
Add to squash.
Pour into buttered dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add alternately small portions of flour and one egg at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add flavoring last.
Bake in stemmed pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese danish muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin cups.
Combine cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg until well blended. In separate bowl, combine muffin mix and milk; stir just until blended.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Top each with about one tablespoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, pumpkin and water in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix and sift all the dry ingredients together. Blend the dry mixture slowly into the wet mixture.
Add nuts and stir until smooth.
Use approximately three 8 x 4-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces and wash.
Drain.
Combine all vegetables.
Mix mayo, sugar, vinegar and salt and pour over vegetables.
Let marinate at least 4 hours in refrigerator, stirring several times.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese.
Cream butter, flour and cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Separate into 4 parts.
Roll in small (1 1/2-inch) rolls. Wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: hershey's black magic cake
directions: Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Cake will be moist.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces and cover with water. Let it come to a boil.
Add dry onion soup mix and other seasonings, if desired.
After the vegetables have boiled for at least 15 minutes, lower heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: chicken quesadilla
directions: Season chicken and cook.
Lightly butter pan.
Put tortilla in pan.
Place chicken, onion and cheese on 1/2 of tortilla and fold in half.
Cook until fairly toasted on one side and flip over. Cook until toasted and cheese is melted.

title: sasha's favorite lentil soup
directions: Bring the first five ingredients to boil in large, covered kettle and simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
Slowly saute onion, carrots and parsley in oil in skillet 15 minutes.
Combine mixtures.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer together for 30 minutes.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Bake at 350° in a covered casserole for 3 hours.
Don't peek! Serve over noodles.

title: cottage cheese whip
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O into cottage cheese and pineapple.
Add oranges (no juice).
Mix in large bowl.

title: aunt bea's perfect cream puffs
directions: Combine boiling water, butter or margarine and salt.
Heat until boiling and stir vigorously, then add flour all at once. Stir constantly until mixture forms a smooth ball and leaves sides of pan clean.
Remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after addition until egg is blended and mixture is smooth. Continue beating until mixture is stiff and breaks when spoon is raised.
Shape on a greased baking sheet with 2 tablespoons, allowing 2 inches between each one.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.	Place on wire rack to cool; fill with cream filling, ice cream or flavored whipped cream. Makes 12 Cream Puffs.
They are wonderful.

title: cream cheese blintzes
directions: Roll bread flat with a rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 c. sugar and egg yolks together.
Spread evenly over the bread and rollup lengthwise.
Dip in melted butter and roll in cinnamon sugar.
Cool in fridge for 20 minutes and then cut into thirds. This can be frozen at this point and stored up to 4 months.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes or bubbly.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Just before serving, slice 3 bananas into salad.
Coconut may also be used.

title: traditional sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly (softened) shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Blend in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into shapes. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or decorate. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until very light brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; set aside.
Beat egg yolks and mix into sugar and flour mixture.
Heat milk, when it comes to a boil, add the sugar and flour mixture to hot milk; stir constantly.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Stir well and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top of pie filling.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch pie pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack washed okra in sterilized jars.
Boil all ingredients together.
Pour over okra and seal.
Cook in hot water bath no longer than 10 minutes.
Do not boil hot pepper; place in jars along with okra, being sure one pod is in each jar.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix all together and pour over folded paper towels (Bounty works best) in a Rubbermaid container.

title: date nut roll
directions: *Colored marshmallows may also be used.

title: cinnamon graham muffins
directions: Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed grape leaves(makes 40)
directions: Drain grape leaves.
Place in a medium bowl.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Drain and discard water.
In large skillet over medium heat, heat vegetable oil.
Add onion, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Add rice and cook 1 minute.
Add 2 cups of the water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir scallions, currants, pine nuts, parsley, salt, mint, dill weed and pepper into rice, until well combined.
Remove from heat.
Select the best grape leaves to stuff; reserve remaining leaves.
On work surface, place a grape leaf, vein side up and stem towards you.
Place about 1 tablespoon of rice mixture close to stem of leaf.
Fold up bottom of leaf, then fold in sides.
Roll to form a rectangular package. Repeat until all stuffing is used.
Use remaining leaves to line the bottom of a 3-quart saucepan.
Place stuffed leaves in a single layer, very close together in pan.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on pizza pan for 7 minutes at 350°. Soften the cream cheese; mix with Ranch dressing, then spread on cooled crescent roll crust.
Put on the fresh vegetables, ending with tomatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Chill at least 2 hours, then cut into slices and serve.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Place 4 graham crackers on a cookie sheet. Place chocolate bars on top of graham crackers. Turn oven setting to broil. Broil until chocolate bars are slightly melted. Remove from oven and place 3 marshmallows on each cracker. Return to oven and broil until marshmallows are slightly brown. Remove from oven and top with remaining graham crackers.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Simmer all ingredients until well done.
Brown flour in shortening to thicken gumbo.
Serve with rice.

title: goody cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add 1/2 of the nuts; blend in flour and remainder of the nuts.
Shape into small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: green beans tuscany style
directions: Trim the beans and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Steam the beans in boiling salt water over low heat until just tender.
Drain thoroughly and cover with a cloth to keep warm. Heat butter and oil over moderate heat.
Stir in 1/2 the sage or parsley and garlic.
Saute 1 minute, then add the beans.
Season to taste with salt and freshly grounded pepper.
Stir over low heat for 5 minutes.
Mix in cheese.
Serve with the remaining herbs sprinkled on top.

title: apricot cream salad
directions: Combine apricots and 2 cups water in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer 12 minutes or until apricots are soft. Drain, reserving liquid.
Prepare jello according to package directions using reserved liquid for part of the water. Refrigerate until partly thickened.
Mash or puree apricots in food processor or blender.
Add to partly thickened jello.
Pour into lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and pepper in boiling water until tender; drain. Stir in tomato soup, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add meats, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Beat 6 eggs; reserve about 1 tablespoon to brush on top of the bread.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Pour this mixture into a "well" you've made in 7 to 8 cups bread flour such as King Arthur's.
Melt 1/4 pound butter in 3/4 cup warm milk and dissolve 2 yeast cakes or packages in 1/4 cup water.
Mix it all together; add anise if desired, then knead your dough for 15 minutes until it is quite dry and elastic.
Add more warm milk or flour as needed.
After two risings, form the dough into 2 loaves in greased cake pans.
When double, slit top with a sharp knife and brush with reserved beaten eggs.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° to 350° about 30 minutes until the bread sounds hollow when you rap it.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place margarine in baking dish and melt; then add other ingredients and mix together.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Place shortening, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Pour boiling water over them.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour.
Blend well, cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
This dough should be in a large mixing bowl as it rises slightly in the refrigerator.
Will keep a week to 10 days and may be used as needed.
About 3 hours before using rolls, roll into desired shape using only enough flour to handle easily.
Place on greased pan and allow to rise at room temperature for about 3 hours or until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix lemon jello, lemon pudding, tapioca pudding and boiling water.
When it starts to thicken, add oranges and crushed pineapple and mix, then add container of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins with salt.
Peel.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and next 4 ingredients.
Mix with a mixer just like mashed potatoes.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart greased pan.
Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated, then cooked.

title: herring pate
directions: Puree in processor.
Put in crock, cover and chill.
Serve on party rye.
Garnish with chopped ripe olives and chopped hard-cooked egg.

title: ham, macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
In saucepan, brown ham in margarine.
Stir in soup, milk and 3/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend macaroni with sauce.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well, then add eggs one at a time. Alternately add flour and sour cream.
Add flavoring.
Use a Bundt pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
For best results, have butter, eggs and sour cream at room temperature.

title: greek lemon cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cake mix and farina.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for length of time given on cake mix package.
Stir in 3/4 cup nuts.
Divide batter evenly between two greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans. Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Place on wire racks, not removing cakes from pans.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers for 24 hours in lime and 2 gallons of water.
Stir once in a while.
Wash 3 times in fresh water.
Soak in clean water 4 hours.
Wash 3 times.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour in pie shells.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo syrup, water and salt together.
Boil until it begins to spin threads.
Add peanuts and cook until they are brown. Take up and add soda.
Beat and pour quickly into a greased pan.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat sugar, syrup and water until sugar dissolves.
While syrup boils, stir in butter and stir often. Heat to 230°.
Add nuts.
Heat to 280°, then stir constantly to 305°.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda; mix well.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets, then stretch by lifting and pulling from edges.
With a fork, loosen from pan as soon as possible and break into pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend flour, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Press evenly in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat together 2 eggs, sugar, salt, lemon juice and flour.
Pour over baked crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes more until golden brown (lightly golden). Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into small bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: brenda's mini rye appetizers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread onto bread slices.
Broil a short time until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: ice cream surprise
directions: Arrange ice cream sandwiches in a 9 x 13 serving dish. Cut if needed. Prick with fork. Pour syrup over ice cream, using as much as desired. Sprinkle with half pecan and candy pieces. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining pecans and candy on top. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Rinse wild rice in cold water. Add with 1/2 teaspoon salt to 2 cups boiling water.
Cook 20 minutes. Add long-grain rice, remaining 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cook 20 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix well pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream the cheese and blend in 3/4 cup sugar.
Add the Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Spread over the cooled pretzels.
Dissolve the jello in boiling water; add frozen strawberries, breaking up with a fork as you stir.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over Cool Whip layer; chill until set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in casserole dish. Add soup, cheese and water chestnuts.
Mix together. Top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: almond brown rice stuffing
directions: Cook almonds in margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat until golden brown.
Add apples, onion, celery, poultry seasoning, thyme and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in rice; cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve or use as stuffing for poultry or pork roast.
Stuffing may be baked in covered baking dish at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, butter, stuffing mix and onion. Add to squash and stir. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 mins.

title: mom's lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic, oregano and basil in skillet.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Arrange layers of sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
End with sauce and Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken; pick off bone.
Boil noodles in chicken broth; drain.
Mix both soups and Ro-Tel together.
Mix noodles, chicken and soup together.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: jam cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a 9-inch tube pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 250° about 1 1/2 hours or when cake leaves sides of pan.

title: heavenly chocolate truffles(microwave)
directions: In glass bowl, mix milk and cocoa.
Stir in chips.
Microwave on High 2 minutes, until chips are melted, stirring after each minute.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Shape balls of about 1 teaspoon of chocolate mixture.
Roll balls in powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs or cocoa mixed into powdered sugar.
Keep mixture cold while rolling into balls.
Chill 1 hour.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: eat more
directions: Cook noodles 10 minutes.
Drain; cook celery and tomatoes together.
Brown meat and onion.
Place all in casserole adding salt, pepper and red pepper.
Add chili powder.
Let simmer in oven at 250° for 2 hours covered.
Serves 6. Sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, stir and add more mayonnaise if necessary.

title: egg nog cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, vanilla and sugar together.
Add baking powder and salt.
Add 1 cup flour, then 1/3 cup egg nog alternately until all are in.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar-nutmeg mixture and bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Beat cream cheese with scallions until smooth.
Spread approximately 1/4 of cheese mixture onto each ham slice.
Starting at long edge, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place rolls on plate and refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours or until firm.
Before serving, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serves 24.

title: parsley bake rice with vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Wash rice.
Add chicken broth, butter and rice.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Stir twice.
Keep rice covered while cooking.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Cook pasta.
Cook ground beef and onions together; drain.
Add all seasonings, tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: rich macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Heat margarine, salt and pepper over medium heat, until margarine melts, stirring constantly.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: In saucepan, heat tomatoes, croutons, yellow corn and 1/2 parmesan until croutons are soggy.	Cut zucchini lengthwise, scoop out middle and stuff with tomato crouton stuffing.	Cover with rest of parmesan.

title: veg casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Crumble the crackers; spread on top.
Melt the oleo; pour over top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sifted all-purpose flour.
Mix well.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in skillet.
Transfer ribs to baking dish.
Place sliced onions over the top.
Mix ketchup, chili powder, liquid smoke, sugar, lemon juice and water and pour over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Baste occasionally. May add more water if too dry.

title: a happy home
directions: Take love and loyalty and mix faith.
Blend it with tenderness and understanding; add friendship and hope.
Sprinkle with laughter.
Bake it with sunshine.
Serve daily with generous helpings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut zucchini and pepper into strips.
Remove skin from chicken and cut into strips.
Heat the oil in a skillet and fry the chicken strips over medium heat until chicken turns white.
Add the remaining ingredients except tortillas and stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Divide the mixture evenly into 6 servings.
Place a serving of chicken mixture in center of each tortilla.
Fold over in half to form the fajita. Serve with fresh salsa.

title: chili corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions. Stir in the chilies, cumin, oregano and sage. Spread in a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, sweetened milk and butter on low heat. Add sifted flour to pan.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon or larger on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool on rack after 2 minutes and hide in tin or they will magically vanish.

title: apple glazed spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces, meaty side down. Combine jelly with vinegar, stirring until jelly dissolves.
Mix in teriyaki sauce and green onions; brush ribs with mixture. Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Discard foil and turn ribs over; brush with remaining sauce.
Bake 30 minutes longer, or until tender, turning ribs over and basting every 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Press hamburger meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread soup over meat. Cover with cheese slices. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven until Tater Tots brown.

title: crab pizza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in mixer. Spread mixture on serving plate. Mix cocktail sauce and chili sauce.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with crab meat. Garnish with parsley (optional).

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook until mixture reaches 270° (if small nuts) or 260° (if large nuts).
Add peanuts and cook until mixture reaches 300°, then add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir and let it rise; stir again and let it rise the second time.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Pull from edges into center until thin.
Let cool.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Adjust quantities of ingredients to taste and number to be served.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Layer the red raspberries on the bottom of a sprayed 9x13-inch cake pan.
Then layer the blueberries on top of the raspberries. Sprinkle cake mix on top of berries.
Pour Diet 7-Up all over the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: cake mix
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large pan.
(A dishpan is good.)
Sift 3 times.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender, fingertips, or a detachable mixer at low speed. (Shortening must be blended uniformly.)
Store in covered container at room temperature.

title: quick and easy candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water in double boiler.
Stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoon on buttered waxed paper and let set.

title: easy roast turkey breast(moist and delicious)
directions: You will need 1 large oven cooking bag (20 x 14-inch) with tie.

title: raisin honey drop cookies
directions: Cream the honey, sugar, butter and egg.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake on upper shelf of moderately hot oven (375°) for 12 to 14 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add crackers to melted margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour; measure and sift with other dry ingredients.
Combine shortening, eggs and orange juice.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Mix only until moistened; do not stir out lumps.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour hot milk over butter. Add sugar and salt; stir well. Crumble yeast in warm water.
Let set.
When milk is cool, add yeast and beaten eggs. Slowly add flour (not necessary to use all the flour).
Knead until smooth.
Let rise double in size.
Knead down and roll out. Spread with butter (oleo). Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and slice; let rise. Bake at 375° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add green peppers, carrots and onion. Sprinkle with garlic and onion powder.
Saute briefly.
Add broth, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar and pineapple with juice.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
If you prefer, rice can be served separately.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well; pour into large pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Fry ground beef until well done.
Pour chili sauce and tomato soup into frying pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in bowl.
Place in boiler the oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Bring this to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, soda and vanilla; mix.
Grease and flour 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup, gelatine and cream cheese until creamy.
Add chopped onion, pepper, celery and mayonnaise.
Add shrimp.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Drop frozen berries in hot mixture. When berries are thawed, add pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a pan.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Spread sour cream over top.
Add the other 1/2 of the mixture over top and refrigerate until congealed.

title: mayonnaise cake(when you are out of eggs)
directions: Sift sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in loaf pan 50 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: italian chicken(method:  foil dinner)
directions: Place 3 tablespoons rice in center of each 8 (12-inch) squares of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle chicken on both sides with 1/2 teaspoon salt and place on rice.
Drain mushrooms; reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Divide mushrooms, zucchini, green peppers and onions into 8 equal portions.
Place one portion over each chicken quarter.
In large bowl, mix together the tomato sauce, 1/2 cup mushroom liquid, oregano and basil; spoon over vegetables and chicken.
Fold foil, using drugstore wrap method.
Be sure seals are tight.
Bake in coals for approximately 1 hour.
When chicken is cooked through, open foil packets, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in melted butter; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit cocktail, bananas, apple, grapes, cherries and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream; refrigerate. Serve cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top; bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a clean dish towel; turn cake out on towel.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of cake.
Roll long side of cake and towel together; let cool.
While cake is cooling, beat together the last 4 ingredients.
Unroll cake; spread this mixture over top.
Roll back up and chill. Slice and eat.

title: simple "strawberry pie"
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together, adding just enough lemon juice to thicken mixture.
Pour into pie shells; garnish with strawberries.

title: heavenly delight
directions: With mixer blend together cream cheese, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Then add Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Put in a pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.

title: spiced warm cider
directions: Combine cider and frozen orange juice in small soup pot. Place cinnamon sticks, cloves and allspice in double layer of cheesecloth, tied with kitchen string.
Lower bag into juice. Simmer mixture, covered, for 1 hour over low heat.
Strain if not using cheesecloth bag.
Serve cider warm (it can be reheated). Recipe makes 33 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, starting at slow speed. Can be frozen and heated as needed.
Serve over pasta or on pizza.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix juices with Tang and instant pudding.
Mix and pour over fruit.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti as directed on package.
Mix onion, tomatoes, green pepper, mustard and sugar in a large bowl.
After draining spaghetti, place on bowl with the other ingredients.
Mix.
Stir in the Creamy Italian dressing.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: irish potato rolls
directions: Mix together potato water, salt and sugar.
Sprinkle yeast on top and stir to dissolve.
Add eggs and shortening.
Mix mashed potatoes in gradually and enough flour for a stiff batter; beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in refrigerator in a greased, covered container. Take out about 2 hours before needed.
Shape and let them rise about 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Butter if you wish before baking at 400° for 15 minutes.
This will keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: chess pie(my original)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually, then remainder of ingredients and beat well with mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook 1 hour at 350° or until pie is set.
Meringue can be used and does improve looks and taste.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour over chicken.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, basting occasionally until done (depends upon what part of chicken you use), 40 minutes. Serve with broiled can peaches, if desired.

title: make ahead cookie mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine butter, salt and baking powder. Using electric mixer, combine well.
Add flour to butter mixture; blend until fine crumbs form, scraping bowl often.
Store in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
Makes 8 cups mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: congealed cherry salad
directions: Drain all fruit together.
Save 1 1/2 cups juice and set aside.
Bring the juice to boil and dissolve gelatin in it.
Add cold water and chill.
Fold in fruit and pecans.
Pour into 6-cup mold or 11 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and let cool until begins to thicken. Wash and chop cranberries,
add sugar, oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Add this to jello mixture and let set.
Real good with dressing.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and measure.
Add liquid and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured tube pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk.
Set aside.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour; dip into soup mixture.
On another piece of waxed paper, coat chicken with stuffing.
Arrange chicken on baking sheet.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
In 1 quart saucepan, combine remaining soup, 1/4 cup milk, parsley and lemon juice.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: lo-cal carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill well before serving.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend ingredients and beat by hand for 2 minutes.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup brown sugar. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and spices.
Sift twice.
Add oil and eggs. Beat with mixer after each.
Fold in plums, vanilla and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Top with confectioners sugar (sift on top).

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the first 6 ingredients about 10 minutes and add shrimp.
Add alternately, in layers, spaghetti and the sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Add the grated cheese on top and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts. Add salt, pepper and seasoned salt to taste. Save broth. Cut chicken into small pieces. Place in baking dish (approximately 9 x 13).

title: fruit glace
directions: Drain all fruits and save 1 1/2 cups fruit juice.
Mix juices, flavoring and pudding mix.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: jalapeo cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Set aside. Lightly beat eggs, milk and oil.
Add flour mixture, cream corn, chilies, cheese and onion; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: grandburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, drop on oiled pan and brown on both sides, gravy or sauce on bun.
Place bouillon cubes in cup of hot water and pour over grandburgers.
Serves 5 to 6.
Cooking time: Browning turn.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until thick, stirring constantly.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Let cool and spread over chocolate cake.

title: sour cream raisin pie(yields one 10-inch pie)
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water until hot and plump.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and cold water.
Add to raisin mixture.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually whisk half of raisin mixture into yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to the rest of the hot raisin mixture; whisk to blend.
Return to stove; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into shell.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush
Oreo
cookies and add to vanilla ice cream.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Store in freezer.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unwrap dinner rolls and lay flat in jelly roll pan to form "crust" for chopped vegetables. Bake 10 minutes until done in a 350° oven. Cool.

title: hot chicken sandwich filling
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove bones from chicken.
Grind chicken.
Bring 2 cups milk to a boil.
Add flour, cold milk, salt and pepper to boiling milk.
Cook until it forms a sauce.
Pour over ground chicken.
If filling is a little thin, add crushed cracker crumbs to thicken.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions in skillet.
Add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Place beans in a casserole.
Pour bacon mixture over top, but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta with vodka and tomato cream sauce
directions: Melt butter and oil in pan.
Add onion and saute until translucent, about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until reduce to almost no liquid remains in pan, about 25 minutes.
Add cream, vodka and red pepper.
Boil until thickened, about 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Place rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: linda's lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger; drain excess fat.
Add spaghetti mix, then tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Let simmer.
Cook lasagne according to package directions.
Drain noodles.

title: pineapple and apricot salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple and apricots.
Save juices. Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Add 1/2 of each juice.
When jello thickens, add 3/4 cup mashed apricots and marshmallows. Refrigerate until firm.
When set, spread the top with the following.

title: fake apple dumplings
directions: Tear bread into stuffing like pieces.
Place in deep dish bowl.
Place applesauce on top of bread.
Place brown sugar on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute.
Pour milk over and serve or place back into microwave to heat milk also.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium-high.
Saute onion (cut in wedges), green pepper (cut in strips) and garlic (diced) for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucini; toss and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple shake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: the school's peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan and large Pyrex cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: oven potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and slice into 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick slices, leaving skins on.
Place in ovenproof pan.
Melt margarine and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May be microwaved for 10 minutes or until potatoes are cooked thoroughly (omit foil and use plastic wrap to top dish).

title: dolores fredette's foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir well until all ingredients are moistened. Wrap in wax paper and chill for at least 1/2 hour.
Then proceed as usual.
This dough will always be flaky, tender and delicious no matter how much it is handled.
Dough can be kept 3 to 4 days in the refrigerator.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Pat into flat crust in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: kentucky prune cake
directions: Blend together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to sugar, eggs and oil. Beat well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, prunes and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Test until toothpick comes out clean.

title: country potato chowder
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp; remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. In the drippings, saute onion and celery until tender. Sprinkle with flour and stir until blended. Gradually add cream. Stir in the potatoes, soup, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the carrots and beans. Cover and simmer 15 minutes longer or until the vegetables are tender. Stir in corn and reserved bacon; heat through. Yields: 12 servings.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in butter in 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: oven-fried vegetables
directions: Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick coating spray.
Set aside.

title: chunky chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pot, saut onion and chicken in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add soups, carrots and mushrooms.
Thin mixture with milk, giving a smooth soup base.
Heat through.
Add Velveeta and allow to melt before serving.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix vinegar and butter in double boiler and boil.
Blend sugar, flour and eggs.
Add slowly to vinegar mixture.
Cook and stir until thick.
Take off heat and add 1 heaping tablespoon mustard and 1/2 pint of mayonnaise.
Makes 1 pint.

title: forty-clove chicken filice
directions: Place chicken pieces in a shallow baking pan, skin side up. Sprinkle all ingredients evenly over chicken.
Squeeze juice from lemon and pour over top.
Cut remaining lemon rind into pieces and arrange throughout chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Rub sugar into meat and cook, covered, over low heat with a little water.
When done, pull apart or shred meat into a heavy saucepan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Makes excellent sandwiches.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 1 1/2 gallon container, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon juice and next 3 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cover and chill.
Pour mixture into a large punch bowl, gently stirring in chilled ginger-ale.
Yield - 1 1/2 gallons.

title: nannie's crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples and run through colander to make 6 cups of applesauce.
Place in crock-pot with remaining ingredients on high for 1/2 hour.
Turn down on low and cook all night with lid on. Next morning, remove lid and cook down to desired thickness.
While hot, pour in jars and cover with hot lids.

title: orange sliced candy cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well and set aside.
Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking soda with buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Mix well.
Add the candy mixture.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes (sometimes a little longer).

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter until fluffy, then add sugar gradually.
Beat until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, chips and nuts until well mixed.
Shape in 2-inch balls. Do not flatten.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets (six per sheet).
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 23 minutes, until golden and edges are light brown.

title: open faced pizza burgers
directions: Cook patties.
Arrange on bun halves.
Add 2 tablespoons pizza sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Mix enough flour to roll well.
Roll out and cut.
Fry in deep oil; Crisco would be a very good oil.

title: stuffed angel food cake(enough for two cakes!)
directions: Fold in the ingredients and pack into cakes.
Place tops on cakes and frost.
Frosting may be tinted.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Add water slowly until mix is not too sticky.
Roll out dough and cut.
Fit around your baking dish.
Pour can of peaches.
Add 2 teaspoons nutmeg.
Roll out crust to top your dish.
Prick crust with fork and sprinkle sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until brown and done.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost (cake is moist).

title: pennsylvania dutch potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes into a large bowl; toss with lemon juice, coating thoroughly.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.
Add melted butter, flour, onions, egg, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Stir to mix well.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello; beat in the oil and milk.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add berries, coconut and pecans.
Make 3 layers and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dark fruitcake
directions: Grease 3 (8 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans or 2 (10 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf dessert pans.
Line bottom and sides of pans with brown paper to prevent overbrowning.
Grease paper.
In a saucepan, melt butter; cool.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, cloves and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add mixed fruits and peels, dates, cherries, raisins, almonds, pecans and pineapple.
Mix until well coated.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add brown sugar, orange juice, molasses and butter; beat until blended.
Stir into fruit mixture.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Boil chicken bouillon and water.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.

title: "my own thing rhubarb cake"
directions: Arrange rhubarb in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin. Top with marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Spread evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until cake tests done. Cool 5 minutes, then turn out of pan, upside down, on serving tray. Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Boil until tender.
Drain water.
Add egg, bread crumbs and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine crumbs, morsels and nuts; mix well. Stir in condensed milk.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Line with waxed paper and grease again.
Spread mixture in pan and bake 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
When inserted toothpick comes out clean, remove from pan and peel off paper.
Cool and cut into bars.
Tightly cover leftovers.

title: super sandwich
directions: Put cheese, Spam, onion and olives in food grinder.
Add tomato paste.
Put in hot dog buns.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time, until brown.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans in margarine in a skillet over low heat; stir constantly (will burn easily).
Heat until brown, but not burned; set aside to cool.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, butter flavoring and part of the milk in a blender.
Add to 1 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer.
Add pecans.
Add remainder of milk, enough to fill the container.

title: fiesta bean dip
directions: Stir together and heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir and serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: salmon and mushrooms
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender (about 3 to 5 minutes).
In remaining butter, stir in flour until well blended.
Add milk and stir slowly until sauce thickens.
Add sauteed onions and mushrooms, wine and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in salmon and cook until heated.
Serve over pasta, egg noodles or rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: *Cook rice as directed but only for 5 minutes.
Add liquid that is left in rice to meat and tomato mixture.

title: cabbage and ground beef casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and boil until tender.
Mash cabbage and measure 5 cups.
Cook ground meat until brown.
Add onions, bell peppers and seasonings.
Stir.
Add cabbage, Ro-Tel and mushroom soup and stir.
Crumble Ritz crackers (all but about 5).
Grate cheese and save 1/4 cup.
Add cheese and crackers to ground meat mixture.
Place in 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining cheese and crackers on top.
Return to oven and bake about 10 minutes.

title: bacon poles
directions: On a plate, place 2 layers of paper towels. Wrap a strip of bacon around each breadstick in a spiral fashion.
Place on paper towel, not touching each other.
Do 8 at a time and arrange in a circle.
Cover with a single layer paper towel and microwave for 4 to 5 minutes on High, until bacon is crisp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground hamburg, both onion soup mix, all of sour cream and bread crumbs, then make into meatballs.
Put in a pan.
Pour in mushroom soup over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes covered with foil.
Bake for 10 minutes uncovered.
Enjoy!

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers, powdered sugar, cocoa, white syrup, chopped nuts and bourbon.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Make a few days ahead of time and store in airtight container.

title: okra-sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until sausage browns; drain.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend together and press in pan.
Bake in slow oven (350°) until light brown.
Cool.

title: fat corn muffins
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt into a small bowl.
Combine eggs, butter and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon batter into greased 3-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or more.

title: horseradish dip for broccoli
directions: Mix all together and serve with steamed broccoli.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Wash crab meat briefly with cold water; remove any pieces of shell and drain. Mix horseradish and chili sauce. Starting with chili sauce mixture, alternate layers of sauce mixture and crab meat over cream cheese bar. Finish with layer of chili sauce. Serve with crackers.

title: ham ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and Miracle Whip good. Add the rest of ingredients. Chill. Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts (finely chopped). Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: applesauce wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let set.
Melt lard and honey.
Add salt and applesauce.
Add this to yeast mixture.
Mix flours and add one cup at a time.
Bake at 300°.
Makes 4 to 5 loaves.
Stays moist and chewy!

title: best old fashioned kolaches
directions: Warm milk to lukewarm, pour into bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 2 cups flour and mix well until smooth.
Place bowl in a warm place and let rise about 30 minutes. Stir in beaten eggs, melted margarine and salt.
Gradually mix in three remaining cups of flour.
Work dough until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until bowl is full or dough doubles in size, about 1 hour.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In 2-quart oblong casserole dish (microwavable), place potatoes and onions.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Stir and microwave 7 more minutes.
Remove and add rest of ingredients.
Stir in.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet applets muffins
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Add sugar gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in egg; mix well. Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in apples. Fill well-greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Dip in melted oleo, then roll in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: birthday icing
directions: Put sugar, shortening and salt in a bowl; mix.
Add water. Beat 30 seconds.
Makes icing for three 8 inch layers.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Mix in Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Spread in pie shells.
Chill for approximately 1 hour.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Combine in large bowl. Do not mash or pack down. (Should be coarse and loose.) Use food processor if you like, but don't make it mushy. Keeps refrigerated for 3 weeks. Can be used for stuffing celery, for sandwiches or on crackers.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, put in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until thick. Stir every 30 minutes.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes (375° may be best if they brown too soon). May be refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix together pears, sugar and pecans.
Set aside 1 hour, stirring often.
Sift all dry ingredients. Add to pear mixture. Mix eggs and oil and stir
in
well with wooden spoon.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool, cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: turkey and tortilla casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine turkey, soup, chilies, salsa, olives, onions and cumin.
Set aside.
Arrange half the tortilla strips in a well-greased shallow 3-quart casserole or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover evenly with half the turkey mixture and all the Jack cheese.
Top with remaining tortilla strips and remaining turkey. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over all.
(At this point, you may cover and refrigerate until next day.)
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix thoroughly together, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in sour milk, hot water, baking powder, flour, cocoa and soda. Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350 for about 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into casserole. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add other ingredients and stir until smooth.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine relish, onion, horseradish, mustard and seasonings. Fold in sour cream.
Cover and chill.

title: microwave cheesy chalupas
directions: In a 2-quart glass mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook on maximum power, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring twice.

title: avice's beans(crock-pot)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook until skins burst.
Leave this water on and mix all ingredients together.
Cook 6 to 8 hours at 250° to 350° (No. 2 on Hi on crock-pot).

title: pink salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and jello.
Then add Cool Whip. Refrigerate, then serve as dessert.

title: crush punch
directions: Mix pineapple and lemon juice together and set aside.
Mix strawberry Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Cook sugar with 3 cups boiling water until syrup turns clear.
Add Jell-O mixture to syrup, then add pineapple-lemon juice.
Add almond extract last and mix well.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn 8 minutes in unsalted water.
Drain.
Cool in cold water.
Cut kernels from ears without scraping.
Measure 1 1/2 quarts kernels.
Use stainless or enamel saucepan.
Combine celery, peppers, onion, salt, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir mustard and turmeric with water to make a paste.
Add to pan.
Stir until it comes to boil and thickens slightly.
Now add corn.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Place in sterile jars.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water.
Seal.
Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: peanut butter frosts
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar and soda in large bowl.
Add butter, peanut butter
and egg; stir until thoroughly blended. (Mixture will be
crumbly.)
Press	in
the
bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges
begin
to
pull away from sides of pan.
Center will be soft.
Cool completely.
Top with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add well beaten eggs.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 350° oven in a Bundt pan, which has been greased well and floured.
Makes a large cake.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and mix all ingredients in large container.
Mix well.
Roll in small pieces.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: excellent zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs for 2 minutes until light and foamy (speed 4 or medium).
Add sugar, vegetable oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Turn mixer on Stir speed (low) and mix until well blended, 1 minute. Stir all ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to
bowl, use Stir speed for 1 minute.
Add nuts and raisins (optional).
Grease two loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave curry turkey divan
directions: Place
frozen
chopped	broccoli
in
1 1/2-quart glass casserole.	Cover
with glass lid.	Microwave for 8 minutes on High, or until partially cooked;
set aside.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Put pineapple in pan with one can of water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Chill.

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in small amount of water.
Crumble cornbread and bread together with fingers.
Add cooked rice.
Add celery, onions, apples, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add enough turkey stock or chicken broth to make a drop (sloppy) batter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour till brown.

title: vegetable-cheese soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter and saute chopped onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add milk and bring just to boiling.
Add frozen vegetables; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Gradually stir in grated cheese until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: crab cakes
directions: *Can used baked dolphin, bass or any other salt water fish desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Grease three 9-inch round pans; flour bottoms. Pour batter in equal amounts into pans.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before frosting.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Add other ingredients except sour cream and cook slowly, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Serve over rice topped with chopped dill pickles, if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Bake meatballs and fry sausage.
Keep grease from sausage.
In a large saucepot, mix tomato puree.
Strain 1 can of tomatoes and use the juice from them.
Add onion, sugar, garlic salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Add meatballs, sausage and sausage grease.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour stirring occasionally, then simmer for another hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Set cream cheese out to room temperature.
Then beat.
Prepare Dream Whip per directions.
Then add powdered sugar.
Beat in cream cheese until creamy.
Add juice.
Put in prepared crust and top with pie filling.
Chill.
For family gatherings, I triple this and put in an 11 x 15-inch pan.

title: roast rabbit with sour cream
directions: Cut rabbit into serving size pieces.
Combine wine, vinegar, onion and spices; bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Salt the rabbit meat liberally and allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Rinse, salt lightly and pour the cooled liquid over the meat.
Store in the refrigerator for 3 days.
Mix the marinade with an equal volume of beef broth and pour into a roaster.
Bake, covered at 325° until tender.
When half done, pour some of the sour cream over the rabbit and continue doing this at intervals until it is gone.

title: fruit dream
directions: Mix all together and pour in a serving dish. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: eggs in a cloud
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut salami in half; arrange, cut side down, around edge of prepared dish.
Arrange bread over bottom of dish.
Arrange cheese slices on top of bread.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, beating until smooth.
Stir in squash and onion.
Add pepper.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into a hot greased skillet, cooking until golden brown (as for pancakes). Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: orange roughy casserole
directions: Place thawed spinach on bottom of dish.
Top with fish pieces. Season.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Beat together sugar and oil and add eggs, one at a time. Stir in pumpkin and orange juice, or whatever liquid you want. Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn into well-greased, floured loaf pans.
Let stand at least 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Let stand in pans for 5 minutes, then turn on racks to cool.

title: teriyaki chicken kabob
directions: In a large frying pan, put 2 tablespoons of oil.
Heat up first, then put sliced chicken breasts in until brown and slightly cooked.
Then put chopped onion and bell peppers and cook for about 5 minutes.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Prepare mix according to package directions (2 cups of Bisquick and 1/2 cup milk).
Knead 8 or 10 times.
Roll out on floured surface to 14-inch circle.
Brush dough with melted butter. Sprinkle dough with cheese.
Cut in 10 wedges (like a pie). Starting at wide end, roll each to form a crescent shape.
Put crescent, point down, on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 10.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.	Let cool and add buttermilk, Cool whip, and nuts.
Mix well and pour into salad mold and chill.	May use 13 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Serves 6-8.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cover cabbage in small amount of water and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Arrange alternate layers of cabbage and corned beef in shallow 2-quart casserole dish. Combine soup, milk, onion, mustard and salt.

Pour over cabbage and corned beef. Toss cubes cut from bread slices with butter. Arrange around edges of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Arrange cheese slices over center of casserole and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: best potato soup yo' ever put in yo' mouth
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes and onion in enough water to cover and cook on medium heat until tender. Add cubes of cream cheese. Remove from heat and stir until cheese is melted. Add soups, butter and spices. Serve hot. Top with onion bits and/or green onion tops.

title: cocoa banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 6 mini and three 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, at medium speed, beat sugar, oil and eggs until blended.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
At low speed, beat flour mixture into egg mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill mini pans 2/3 full and smaller pans 1/2 full.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.
Wrap in plastic wrap and then foil.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Insert cloves about 1/2-inch apart into orange.
Place in shallow baking pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pierce orange in several places with fork.
In large saucepan, combine apple juice, lemon juice, cinnamon sticks and baked orange. Cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and orange.
Pour into heatproof punch bowl.
Makes 16 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, soups, milk and mushrooms.
Place in a greased casserole or pan (13 x 9-inch).
Layer chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, until chicken is brown and tender.
Serves 6.

title: taste treats
directions: Melt
almond
bark
in double boiler or microwave, then pour over
cereal,
nuts
and
pretzels
in a square keeper or large container.
Mix until evenly coated, turn onto wax paper to cool and dry.
Break in small pieces when dry.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix water, Karo syrup, and sugar in a saucepan.
Boil to 310 degrees, stirring occasionally.
While it's boiling, cover two cookie sheets with powdered sugar.
After it reaches 310, turn off heat.
Add food coloring and flavor.
Stir until blended. Pour evenly into two cookie sheets and let it sit until it hardens. Crack with the end of a butter knife.
Store in an airtight container.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until done.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle diced ham, sausage or crumbled bacon and cubed Velveeta in pie shell.
Beat eggs in bowl; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake about 30 minutes longer or until quiche tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: beau monde dip(low calorie)
directions: In blender cream cottage cheese until smooth.
Add onion soup mix,
dill weed, lemon juice and Beau Monde spice.
Blend until mixed well.

title: flautas
directions: For each flauta, top tortillas with 1 slice of meat and 1 tablespoon
of
each
cheese.
Roll tortilla tightly, pierce with toothpick
and
drop
into
hot oil until lightly brown. Remove to paper towel to drain.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place breasts on foil.
Put other ingredients on top.
Wrap and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cut open top and brown additional 10 minutes.
These are excellent made ahead in bulk and frozen.

title: chip dip
directions: Beat until smooth and then add onions to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey and set aside.
Mix refried beans and Bisquick to form a paste.
Use mixture to layer (form a crust) in baking pan.
Layer meat over mixture followed by salsa, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and chopped green onions.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Then mix in rest of ingredients (using dry jello).
Fresh strawberries may be used for garnish.
For variety, use orange or lemon jello and mandarin oranges instead of strawberries.

title: make believe champagne
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes. Add fruit juice. Chill. At serving time, stir in ginger ale. (Put ice cubes in punch bowl.) Serve with assorted hors d'oeuvres.

title: mock lasagne casserole
directions: Brown the meat; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, pepper, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half each macaroni, cottage cheese, shredded cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Mix fruit together in a baking dish.
Cover with one yellow cake mix (unprepared). Pour over the top one stick of melted oleo. Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: jello cake
directions: Empty cake mix in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat 3 minutes until smooth and creamy.
Line bottom of tube pan with wax paper.
Pour into pan and bake 50 -55 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on wire racks.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Chop onion and ham.
Combine cream cheese and grated Cheddar. Work into a large ball.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, measuring syrup (add water to make 1/2 cup).
Stir in gelatin with lemon juice.
Blend in mayonnaise and chill until thick.
Whip cream and fold fruits, nuts and whipped cream into gelatin.
Pour into 2 freezing trays.
Freeze until firm, at least 3 to 4 hours. To serve, slice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Make the dressing in a jar and shake well.

title: southwest shoe peg corn
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese; stir over heat until melted. Add Shoe Peg corn, green chilies, sugar and salt.
Pour into buttered casserole. Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Can be done on stove in saucepan, if you are in a hurry.

title: pineapple casserole(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 325° in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: flan(egg custard - spain)
directions: Boil milk with vanilla or cinnamon.
When the milk is coddled, add egg yolks, 2 egg whites, 9 1/2 tablespoons sugar and pinch of salt.
Beat well.
Boil 4 tablespoons of sugar with 4 tablespoons of water, stirring constantly, in a flan mold, until the syrup turns into caramel.
Let cool.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop spoonfuls in frying pan and fry.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Heat vinegar and honey in a heavy small saucepan, over low heat, stirring until honey dissolves.
Pour into a bowl and cool. Whisk in mayonnaise, mustard, onion, parsley and salt.
Gradually whisk in oil.
(Can be prepared 3 days ahead, covered and refrigerated; bring to room temperature before using.)
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add apples.
Mix well.
Pour into 10 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test by putting toothpick in it. If comes out clean, it's done.
Drizzle with powdered sugar, when cool.

title: saucy turkey manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti and drain.
Stir together sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Add turkey, onion, parsley, salt and pepper. Blend well.
Spoon turkey mixture into shells.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine process cheese and milk over medium heat, stir constantly until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth. Pour cheese sauce over manicotti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pikes peak potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix cream with broth and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for another 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from egg whites; arrange whites on plate or container.
Sieve egg yolks and combine with remaining ingredients except avocado; mix well.
Refill egg whites with egg yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika.
Garnish with avocado. Half of recipe may be stored in a container.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.
Mix dressing according to package directions.
Pour over salad and refrigerate.

title: baked custard(for diabetics)
directions: Lightly beat eggs, then add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour mixture into five 6-ounce custard cups and place cups in pan containing 1 inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: fresh okra muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients.
Add to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in okra and onion.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in the water until tender (20 to 25 minutes). Remove meat in strips; sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper and toss, then set aside.

title: pecan butter fingers
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Gradually mix in flour.
Stir in salt, vanilla and pecans.
Using a level tablespoon of dough, shape into 2-inch long fingers.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven and cool completely.

title: rhubarb strawberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer, combine sugar and margarine.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until mixture is creamy (1 to 2 minutes).
Add rhubarb, yogurt and eggs. Continue beating until well mixed.
By hand, stir in flour, baking soda and cinnamon just until moistened.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pan.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
While still warm, brush top of muffins with strawberry preserves.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and 1/3 cup margarine.
Bake in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes. While still hot, put marshmallows on top.
Stir together Karo, 1/4 cup margarine, peanut butter chips and vanilla.
Heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in peanuts and cereal.
Pour over marshmallow covered cake.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Spread in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat together until smooth (1 minute with mixer or 15 seconds in blender): milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and cheese.
Bake 8 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: happy hour special
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place in 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and stir in garlic.
Pour over biscuit pieces, making certain that all are well covered. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits spring back when lightly touched.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic powder together and drain. Mix the rest of ingredients together except chips and cheese in slow cooker and add hamburger.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve in bowl with chips and cheese on top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Into bowl, sift flour, soda and salt.
Add caraway seed, sugar and raisins.
Mix melted butter, beaten eggs and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture.
Form into a round loaf; place in round 2-quart pan.
With a knife, cut a cross on top of loaf.
After removal from oven, rub top with butter while still warm.
Cool; wrap in foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter. Mix thoroughly.
Add 1 container of Cool Whip until well blended. Fill pie shell.
