Frost with the remaining Cool Whip.

title: chrusciki(angel wings)
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add cream and sugar; beat well. Add flour, salt and cinnamon.
Roll small amount of dough at a time to a little less than 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch strips, cutting ends diagonally.
Make a lengthwise slit and pull one end through.
Fry in hot deep fat at 350° for about 2 minutes or until slightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.
When cold, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crab louis dip
directions: Mix and spread on plate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add cream cheese and continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour with baking powder and add with soft cream cheese.
Add flavorings. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup and salt in 2-quart bowl. Cover bowl loosely with Saran Wrap so steam can escape. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes until boiling. Uncover and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes until hard-ball stage is reached. Drop small bit into cold ice water to see if it will form a hard ball. Beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites. Have electric mixer on high speed. Add vanilla flavoring. Continue to beat at last 6 to 7 minutes until candy holds shape. Drop by small teaspoons on wax paper. Cool.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 10 minutes or low heat.
Add surimi, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Simmer until heated through.
Sprinkle with scallions.

title: munster pie
directions: Beat egg, add flour.
Add 1\2 of the milk, blend.
Add remaining milk, cheese, salami, onion, salt and pepper.
Grease 9-inch glass pie plate.
Pour mixture.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 min.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 25 min.

title: chuck roast
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour over the roast.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: light batter for vegetables or meat
directions: Beat egg and water and blend with rest of ingredients.
Dip meat or vegetables and fry until golden brown.
Great for boneless chicken breast.

title: heavenly hash christmas candy
directions: Cut up dates and marshmallows.
Cut up nuts (not too fine). Melt chocolate and butter and pour over rest.
Press in large pan. Let cool.
Cut in squares.
(Mixing up with your hands is much easier.)

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla, eggs and oil.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Add cherries and nuts.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato-green pepper salad
directions: Dip tomato in boiling water; peel, remove seeds and chop. Remove seeds and chop green pepper 1/2 inch.
Peel, remove seeds and chop cucumber.
Chop green onion.

title: chili dip
directions: In a glass 13 x 9-inch pan, spread cream cheese.
Top with chili and add green chilies evenly.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake until hot and cheese is melted or may be heated in microwave.

title: egg custard
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch pie pan, generously.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into pie pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Invert 2nd crust and seal the two crusts together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until crust is brown.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruit and place in a 2-quart buttered baking dish. In a small mixing bowl, combine cornstarch, curry powder, cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over fruit.

title: lazy day coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream, mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to batter and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of mixture over cake and swirl through batter.
Sprinkle the rest on top.
Cover and chill overnight. Uncover and bake in 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shortcut stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In medium skillet over medium high heat, heat oil.
Add beef and cook until beef is browned and juices evaporate, stirring often.
Add soup, broth, water and worcestershire.
Heat to a boil. Stir in pasta.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 15 minutes or until pasta is done, stirring often.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter, white and brown sugar.
Then add water, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, then add chocolate chips; mix again.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You can sprinkle additional chocolate chips on top while hot to frost.
Cut in bars.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix well, first 4 ingredients.
Melt in double boiler, milk and caramels.
Pour 1/2 of cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over this and pour the rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: country store baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water in a 4-quart stockpot.
Bring to a boil; boil 10 minutes.
Drain, reserve liquid.
Heat oven to 325°. Place half of bacon and half of onions in bottom of 4-quart bean pot or small casserole with cover.
Add half of beans, remaining onions, then remaining beans; top with remaining bacon.
Mix molasses, brown sugar, salt, pepper and ginger with reserved bean liquid; pour over beans.
Add enough water to cover beans by 2 inches.
Cover and bake 4 to 4 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add up to 3 1/2 cups hot water as needed to keep beans moist. Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon-sizzler appetizers
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: peanut paddies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft ball (235°), stirring often. Take off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until candy thickens.
Drop on waxed paper or buttered oven liners.

title: cold asparagus soup(easy, elegant and flavorful)
directions: Pour asparagus with liquid into blender; add all ingredients. Blend on high until smooth.
Chill.
Variations can include can of string beans and garlic powder or spice of your choice.
A dollop of sour cream or yogurt can be added when serving.

title: chocolate pecan cake
directions: Place in square pan the butter and vegetable oil; add cocoa to butter and oil, then water.
Bring 1 cup of water to boil.
Remove from heat; add flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Stir with fork.
Pour in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, make icing (recipe follows).

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Cook all the ingredients together until garlic and parsley are done.
Drop in shrimp until done.
It makes a wonderful gravy. Throw the shrimp away and eat the gravy with French bread.
(Only kidding!
Keep the shrimp.)
The gravy is wonderful.
Easy easy!

title: garden ratatouille
directions: Fry bacon until lightly browned.
(Drain off excess fat.) Add olive oil and heat.
Add chopped peppers, onion and garlic; saute for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot. Add ground turkey and next 3 ingredients; cook until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Wipe drippings from skillet.
Return turkey mixture to skillet; add Italian seasoning and next 4 ingredients. Cover and cook over medium heat 30 minutes, stirring often.
Combine egg whites, cottage cheese and parsley; set aside.
Coat a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place 5 noodles in bottom of dish.
Top with half each of turkey mixture and cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bones.
Add to chicken both cans of soup and mix well.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture. Pour enchilada sauce over filled tortillas.
Top with both kinds of cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: toasted coconut dessert
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well all ingredients together.
Use paper liners in tiny muffin pans.
Bake 18 minutes.
May be frozen in sealed containers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place bacon on top.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 3 hours.

title: riced chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a large cake pan. Add the rice.
Mix the soups and milk.
Place chicken on rice. Cover with liquid.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup and onion soup

title: john's curry
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter.
Set aside.
Brown meat in frying pan. Transfer to a large pot.
Make a gravy in frying pan with drippings.
You may want to thicken it with small amount of flour. Add all ingredients to meat and simmer until meat is done. Cook rice as directed on package.
Cut up boiled egg, 1 tomato, pineapple, banana, raisins and coconut and place in small dishes. Serve on top of curry and rice.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice and crushed pineapple (including juice).
Chill until partially firm.
Whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold into gelatine mixture.
Spread into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Break bits of angel food cake and spread gelatine mixture.
Repeat until all cake and gelatine mixture are used.
Chill.
Prepare third envelope of Dream Whip; spread on top of cake and cover with coconut.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: diabetic-peanut butter pie
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine and mix with cracker or cereal crumbs. Pat into bottom of 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let crust cool at room temperature.

title: sweet dream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar at high speed of an electric mixer 1 minute. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves (about 2 to 4 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Place in oven and immediately turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for at least 8 hours.
Carefully peel cookies from foil.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all together in a large jar.
Let soak in it a clove of garlic, cut into and a slice of onion.
Let stand for a day or more and shake once in a while.
Then remove onion and garlic. Put into bottle.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs to form a thin layer of crust in an oblong baking dish; set aside. In saucepan, cook to a custard 1 stick margarine, eggs and sugar. Cool completely and spoon over crust.
Place sliced bananas over custard mixture. Spread crushed pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Top with cherries. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch chips.
Stir until melted and well blended.
Add orange extract and rind (can omit this).
Add nuts.
Pour in greased, 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/3 pounds candy.

title: cut-it-short torte
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350°.
Cool.
Split cake into 3 layers.
Spread 1/3 of whipped topping and 1/3 of pie filling between each layer and on top.
Chill until set.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water and oatmeal; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat until fluffy the butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add oatmeal mixture and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove from pan. Top immediately with frosting.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Mix vinegar, syrup, water and vanilla; set aside.
Cream margarine, oil and 1/3 tablespoon sugar.
Alternate dry ingredients and wet ingredients into creamed mixture.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: purple cow
directions: Put 2 scoops of ice cream in a tall glass.
Fill the glass with grape soda.
Stir.
You can also make an Orange Cow by using orange soda or a Brown Cow using root beer or cola.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Cook broccoli until done.
Add onion and pepper.
Add all 3 soups.
Add 3 cans of water.
Add 1 jar Cheez Whiz and 1/2 jar of salsa or jalapeno Cheez Whiz.
Heat and serve.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and continue to beat until light. Add vanilla and flour; fold in nuts.
Shape into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: layer or 24 hour salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a low bowl and sprinkle a little salt and pepper as you go.
Layer lettuce, green pepper, celery, onion, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Press peas down tightly.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise over all.
Place slices of tomatoes on top of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with grated cheeses, then crumble cooked bacon and chopped hard-boiled eggs over top. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix eggs and pie filling.
Add dry cake mix.
Spread in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with icing.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan or two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
In a large bowl at medium speed, beat butter until smooth.
At low speed, add sugar gradually, beating well.
Clean beaters.
Blend in honey at low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium high speed after each addition.
On a large sheet of waxed paper, combine cinnamon, cloves, allspice, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, salt and 3 1/4 cups flour.
Add blended dry ingredients to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Toss reserved 1/2 cup with raisins, figs and almonds; add to mixture.
Pour batter into pan.
Cut through batter with knife to distribute evenly.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester poked in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 30 minutes.
Turn out on a rack to cool.
Top with your own favorite frosting.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes.	Slice onion and separate into rings.
Mix together mayonnaise, vegetable oil and vinegar.

title: honeymoon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: tuna salad
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Mash yolks and finely chop whites.
Mix yolks with garlic, oil and bread until smooth.
Add pepper, vinegar and salt.
This is the dressing.

title: lazy chicken
directions: In greased (spray generously with Pam) baking dish, evenly spread uncooked rice. Place chicken on rice, skin side up. Mix dry onion soup, water and soup. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Boil milk and flour together until thick and smooth.
Cool. Beat together next 3 ingredients.
Add boiled flour and milk to Crisco mixture.
Beat at high speed until very fluffy.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with Wesson oil and sugar.
Add flour sifted with other dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; add dates, nuts and apples; mix thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Can put a custard sauce over top.

title: debbie's oriental dip with snow peas
directions: Trim ends of snow peas.
Place snow peas in vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam about 1 minute.
Do not overcook.
Should still be crisp.
Remove snow peas; rinse with cold water and chill for about 2 hours.

title: american country fare
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on package.
Cook sausage in large skillet in water over medium heat for six minutes.
Add vegetables and oregano.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni dinner and mix lightly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the meat with oil and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge walnut ripple layer cake
directions: Preheat
oven
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar,
cocoa, baking soda, salt, buttermilk, shortening,	2 eggs
and
teaspoons vanilla extract.
Beat on low speed until blended, scraping bowl constantly.	Beat 3 minutes on
high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into 2 paper lined, greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix
coconut
and
pecans.
Spread in a
x
13-inch greased pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour
on top of coconut pecan mixture.
In a
saucepan
put
1 stick margarine and cream cheese.
Heat until
mixture is warm enough to stir in the box of confectioners
sugar.
Spoon over top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45
minutes.
Do
not
cut cake until cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and mix with chopped shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dip chicken into flour and coat.
Heat butter and oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken slowly on both sides until cooked.
Remove to warmed platter.
Stir lemon juice and wine in pan with drippings to deglaze.
Stir thoroughly to loosen all pieces. Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and garnish platter with pimento and lemon wedges.

title: pasta with tomatoes
directions: Combine cooked and drained macaroni with the Parmesan cheese. Add the tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Toss and serve.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Simmer chicken in salt water, in a covered pan, until tender (a frying chicken will take about 45 minutes).
Remove chicken from broth; cool enough to handle.
Remove skin and bones; chop meat.
Add water to broth (if needed) to make 5 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, vegetables and spices.
Simmer, covered for 20 minutes.
Add noodles; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peach layered gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pie filling; mix well and pour into pans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Pour Italian dressing over fresh, sliced tomatoes.
Marinate 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and fresh basil.

title: slaw
directions: Let cabbage and salt stand 45 minutes to 2 hours.
Squeeze out all the water.
Boil sugar, white vinegar and water.
Add celery, green pepper, celery seed and dry mustard or mustard seed to cabbage.
Pour hot vinegar over slaw while hot.
Keeps about a month or may be frozen.

title: stir-n-roll biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475° (very hot).
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into a measuring cup, but don't stir, then pour all at once into flour.
Stir with a fork until the mixture clears sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball.
Smooth by kneading dough about 10 times without additional flour.
With the dough on waxed paper, press out 1/4-inch thick with hands.
For higher biscuits, roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli a la greque
directions: Cut broccoli into serving pieces.
Cook until tender.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine next 8 ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Turn broccoli once.
To serve, arrange on platter; sprinkle with crumbled Feta cheese.
Garnish with tomato wedges and hard-boiled eggs (quartered).

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Gradually add flour mixture, beating well. Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza cheese meat loaf
directions: Crush crackers and combine with beef, 2/3 of the can of tomato sauce, egg, onion, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Mix well and press out into a large rectangle on waxed paper.
Dump shredded cheese in a pile near one end of the rectangle, and sprinkle a little along middle of rectangle.
Start at the end where the pile of cheese is and roll up like a jelly roll.
Be sure to "seal" ends and smooth end seam into loaf.
Be careful not to poke a hole in loaf.
Place seam side down in loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove from oven, drain off grease.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over loaf and return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon and pour in a casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large bowl except Kisses. Mix on low speed until well blended.
Make into balls about 3/4 inch.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Take out of oven and place a Kiss in each cookie.
Place back in oven long enough to soften Kiss.

title: crabby english wedges
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on English muffin halves.
Cut muffins in quarters or eighths and arrange on cookie sheet. Broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Can be prepared the night before and refrigerated.
Broil just before serving.
Excellent appetizer.
Can freeze for up to 30 days and use as needed.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Using fork, add water, 1 tablespoonful at a time.
Roll out on floured surface. If recipe calls for a baked pie shell, prick and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 pie shells or 1 double crust.

title: french bread
directions: Combine 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until margarine melts.
Cool slightly.
Gradually add liquid to flour mixture, beating well at high speed of mixer.
Beat an additional 2 minutes at high speed. Add 2 cups of flour, beating well.

title: baked potatoes and onions
directions: Saute cut up onion in butter.
Scrub potatoes and slice thin (don't peel).
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle with salt. Pour butter and onion over potatoes; bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Baste occasionally while baking.

title: bubbly iced tea
directions: In a large pitcher, pour in the water. Add iced tea mix and stir until well dissolved. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Add carbonated drink, stir and pour over crushed ice in tall glasses. Tasty!

title: apple squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to shortening mixture and mix to form crumbs.

title: hamburgers with stuffing
directions: Mix milk and ground beef and divide into 4 or 5 patties, 6 inches in diameter.
In the center of each patty put 1/4 cup stuffing.
Mold the meat around the stuffing to form a ball. Place in 8 x 8-inch dish and add the soup.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook on 375° griddle. Serves 2.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, cool and dice in large bowl.
Add parsley; toss.
Cook bacon (cut into small pieces) until crisp, add onion (chopped) and cook until onions are done.
Drain off some of the bacon fat.
Add flour and cook until bubbly.
Stir in vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, simmer 2 minutes, pour over potatoes and toss.
Enjoy!

title: hungarian potato soup
directions: In a large soup pot or Dutch oven, heat the margarine over medium heat.
Add the onions and garlic; saute until very soft, about 10 minutes.
Stir in the potatoes, water, salt, paprika, thyme, caraway and cayenne.
Bring just to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mash the potatoes slightly with a long-handled fork and season with black pepper to taste.
Makes 8 servings.
This soup is delicious on a cold day.

title: frozen black velvet
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; let stand 10 minutes.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Set out cream cheese until room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Garnish with parsley.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar together well. Add to this eggs, milk, butter and flavoring after they have been mixed in a separate bowl. Next add persimmon pulp to all of the ingredients; mix well and pour into a 9 x 12 pan and bake at 350° until a knife inserted comes out slightly moist. Eat after cooled to room temperature or after refrigerated. Keep in refrigerator to store.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter; add sugars and beat well.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Alternately add dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in chips.
For each cookie drop 1/4 cup dough onto greased cookie sheet; spread into pumpkin shape.
Add a bit more to form stem. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cookies are lightly browned.
Remove from sheet and cool.
Can be decorated using icing, candies, nuts or more chips.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook the first 7 ingredients over double boiler until thick. Chill.
Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put this mixture in bottom of the pie shell.
Place raisin mixture on top.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: carolyn's heavenly, heavenly salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and place in buttered casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients except Cheddar cheese and pour over broccoli.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
May add paprika on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spanish rice
directions: Steam all vegetables together until tender.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Heat through.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening, then water and eggs. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Slice your favorite pound cake; butter each side and grill in skillet (electric skillet works great).
Remove from skillet and top each piece with vanilla ice cream and drizzle the top with hot fudge topping and honey.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
This is certainly not dietetic, but it is gggrrreat.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until brown and settled.

title: club chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add evaporated milk, chicken broth and water.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add rice, chicken and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through completely.
If desired, top with 1/4 cup slivered almonds. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fruit or pound cake cubes, if desired. Makes 3 cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together for 5 minutes at full boil.
Remove from heat quickly and thoroughly stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda (this will change the consistency).
Pour mixture over popped corn; mix well.
(But be very careful, candy mixture is very hot and will burn fingers if touched.)
When well combined, bake in slow oven at 225° to 250° for 1 hour, stirring at 15 minute intervals.
Pour out to cool completely, then store in tight containers.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: coating for chicken
directions: Beat and let stand.
Coat chicken.
Turn chicken over every 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick and easy apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with strips of bread.
Melt margarine and add sugar and egg. Mix and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked sausage and rice
directions: Crumble sausage and fry until brown; then mix with other ingredients.
Pour into large casserole, cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Stir in all of the ingredients, except pecans.
Bring to a rolling boil; add pecans.
Let cool until bubbles form on top. Take off fire.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Dip out by teaspoon on greased surface until cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add soup and milk.
Pour into a baking dish.
Spread cheese on top of hamburger mixture.
Then place Tater Tots on top of cheese uniformly.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: dessert crepes
directions: Place the ingredients in the blender in the order listed. Cover and blend at top speed for 1 minute.
Let stand at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon crisp; pour off all but 2 tablespoons of grease and saute onion.
Drain liquid from clams; set clams aside.

Add water to clam juice to make 1 quart and combine with all other ingredients except bacon bits and clams in a 4-quart saucepan; simmer together for 30 to 40 minutes, then add bacon bits and clams and simmer about 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam, or brush with oil.
Heat skillet and brown chicken quickly.
Place in baking dish.
Mix Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and bake until melted.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with rotini.

title: swamp rice
directions: Fry out the sausage.
Cook rice per directions on box.
Drain excess fat from sausage and set aside.
In small amount of fat remaining, saute the onions until tender.
Add flour to onions and stir to moisten, not brown.
Add chicken broth and juice from the mushrooms to the mixture in the frying pan, stirring constantly until gravy consistency.
Mix rice, mushrooms, sausage and gravy thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in casserole dish.
May be topped with slivered almonds.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine butter or margarine and sugar; cream well. Add flour and potato chips. Mix in walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except grated cheese and onions. Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Blend peppers until liquid in blender.
Combine peppers, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Take off heat and add Certo and food color.

title: galley beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Put meat and remaining ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 3 or 4 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Put in small containers and store in freezer.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Make jello as directions.
Add bananas, marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Allow to set.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook sausage and pour off fat.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Grate cheese.
Reserve 1 egg yolk and beat with water.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into pie shell.
Top with pie crust.
Brush top crust with egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a very sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger. Add beef and toss. Set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: one-dish chicken broccoli rice
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time, until browned.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until tender-crisp.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; put into casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers over mixture; top with pats of butter. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot, about 30 minutes.

title: ugly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat first three ingredients with mixer until smooth.
This will be thick.
Spread in pan.
Set to the side.

title: bride's favorite ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and ice cream.
Stir until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: franklin hunley's vanilla ice cream
directions: Scald one can of milk and one can of water.
Beat 4 eggs; add salt, sugar and flour.
Pour into scalding milk and cook until thick.
Then add other milk and water as desired.
He used a can of water to each can of milk.
Add flavoring after mixture is poured into freezer.
(He also sometimes mixed a little lemon flavoring with the vanilla, seemed to downplay the sweet taste he said.)

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Blend mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 320°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil sugar and milk over high heat and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Beat in peanut butter and marshmallow.
Pour into buttered platter to cool.

title: hot sausage appetizers - "sausage balls"
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Shape into one-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 servings.

title: grandma's salve
directions: Melt and pour
into
2	quarts	of
cold water 9 times, changing the water.
Each time
squeeze
most of the water out with hands.
At last heating,
add	a piece of camphor gum the size of a small hickory
nut.
Break into small pieces to melt more readily.
Roll into balls.
While
doing so, work out the particles of water, keeping a dry rag to wipe hands on as they become moist.
To apply,
reheat before application.
Store in waxed paper.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pineapple over dry pudding mix.
Mix well; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: toasted coconut frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of oleo in skillet; add coconut. Stir constantly over low heat until golden brown and spread on absorbent paper to drain and cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons oleo and cream cheese.
Add milk and beat in sugar gradually.
Add vanilla. Stir in 1 3/4 cups coconut.
Ice cake and sprinkle top of cake with remaining coconut.

title: chocolate "poor man's" cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix by hand, adding one ingredient at a time.
Add coffee last.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cream Frosting.

title: initial starter for sourdough bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Mix last two ingredients well.
Then mix all together.
Store in refrigerator and feed every 3 to 5 days.

title: zesty black bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in 3-quart saucepan until crisp.
Remove to paper towels.
Add onion and garlic to drippings; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add beans, broth, water, picante sauce, salt and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon into bowls.
Dollop with sour cream, if desired.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbled bacon.
Serve with extra picante sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry pretzel delight
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, sugar and margarine well.
Press into 9-inch dish. Prepare topping mix according to directions.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip until well blended.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling on top. Refrigerate.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil until clear. Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool. Place 4 cups fresh berries in baked shell.
Pour mixture slowly over the berries.
Chill until firm.

title: polish sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well, but lightly.
Shape into patties.
Can be made into links with sausage stuffer.

title: mary caggiano's eggplant appetizer
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; put in colander.
Sprinkle salt on and let drain to remove bitter taste.
Heat oil in large skillet; add onion and saute until tender, but not brown.
Add eggplant and tomato; cook slowly, stirring often, until thick, about 15 minutes.
Add vinegar and spices.
Chill.
Makes about 3 cups. Serve as an appetizer with crackers or as a side dish with meat.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all at once for about 5 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pans or regular cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: "party turnovers" (crescent roll-ups)
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat and soup.
Blend in cheese. Separate rolls in package and cut in half.
Place spoonful of meat mixture into crescent triangle, fold over and seal.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Dip into hot mustard.
Can be frozen.
Makes 48 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together until hard ball forms when syrup is dropped into cold water and it doesn't stick to teeth.
Good luck!

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberry halves and kiwi slices. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and salt; cut in Crisco.
Add the milk gradually, just until dry mixture is moistened.
Form into a ball.
Divide in half and roll out to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Peel the apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut in butter with remaining flour and sugar, making fine crumbs.
Fill pastry-lined pie pan alternately with sliced apples and cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Using a glass bowl (clear if you have one), place marshmallows on bottom and pour gelatin over.
Add pineapple and sliced bananas.
Let gel.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Put all ingredients in a frying pan and simmer, covered, for about 10 minutes on medium heat.
If dry mushrooms desired, remove lid after first 10 minutes.
Cook 10 more minutes or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
(This mixture boils over.
Bake in large dish or put pan under dish to save your oven.)
Serve warm only.

title: mom's cake filling(pineapple)
directions: Mix all together and cook in saucepan until thick.
Pour over cake while hot.
Cook cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Be sure to take the batter out before you put the cake in to bake.

title: honey-avocado butter
directions: Blend or whip avocado and honey.
Cover mixture with plastic wrap placed directly on surface of the spread.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Delicious on hot cornmeal muffins or English muffins.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Stir-fry the chopped celery and onions in the oil. Add 3 cups water and barley and boil 15 minutes. Add carrots with their water and chicken. Add more water (3 cups?) if needed. Heat, then add chicken base, 1 tablespoon at a time until broth has a good flavor.

title: coca-cola icing
directions: Heat oleo, cocoa and Coke to boil; remove from heat and add powdered sugar. Mix, then add pecans. Pour over cake.

title: 4-layer delight
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the margarine, flour and pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Arrange
apples in an ungreased 2-quart glass casserole or square
glass baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients;
sprinkle
over apples.
Microwave apples (uncovered) until they are tender, about 12 minutes.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Boil water in pan on stove or in microwave (must be boiling).
Add bacon grease to water. Pour into cornmeal, flour and sugar mixture.
Stir until well mixed (about 15 seconds).
Shape in patties and fry about 2 to 3 minutes in very hot oil until golden.
Makes 6.
Watch them disappear!

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer slowly for 1/2 hour or more until tender.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Drain the beans, reserve the cooking water and add onions, molasses, catsup, dry mustard, salt, bean water or beer, vinegar, curry powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a greased casserole.
Decorate with sliced salt pork.
Bake covered for 6 to 9 hours.
If they become dry, add well seasoned stock or reserved bean water.
Uncover for the last hour of cooking.
Good Luck!

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in about 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Do not season.
Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Alternate mixture with tortillas in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Mix in chili and heat thoroughly.
Pour ingredients into casserole baking dish.
Top mixture with crumbled Fritos, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is slightly brown.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix thoroughly until the butter and milk are gone.
Then roll into little balls.
Put in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add butter to crackers.
Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Beat eggs; add to squash.
Add milk, sugar, salt, butter and onion; mix well in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add crackers and cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, water chestnuts, onion, Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpernickel dill dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayo, dill, onion flakes and salt. Let sit and chill for about an hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Use equal parts of catsup and Coca-Cola. Mix and add to your taste the remaining ingredients.

title: elsie's crispy sweet pickles
directions: Note:
There is no cooking of the pickles.
Takes approximately 12 days.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine milk, eggs, onion, salt and pepper in large bowl. Stir in stuffing mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Cook mushrooms and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done. Combine golden mushroom soup and sour cream; warm and serve over the meat loaf.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix meat, mixed vegetables and soup in casserole dish.
Mix flour, butter and milk together; pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bernie's banana bread
directions: Combine bananas, sugar, egg and melted butter.
Mix in dry ingredients until flour is moistened.
Using greased loaf pan, bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla french toast
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs; add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt. Soak bread for 30 seconds on each side.
Cook on a greased griddle (or, my antique cast-iron skillet) until golden brown on both sides and cooked through.
Serve with syrup or cinnamon-sugar. Yield: 2 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Take half of that and put in a 9-inch baking dish.
Reserve the other half for later.
Take rhubarb and put over mixture in baking dish. Cook the white sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and water until thick. Pour immediately over rhubarb and put rest of crumbs on.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: puerto rican pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
In large bowl, add the milk to the bread.
Let set for 2 hours.
Add eggs, butter,
vanilla, salt and sugar; beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Add the raisins.
Pour into a 12 x 10-inch buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: dutch apple cream cake(serves 8)
directions: For crust, combine cake mix and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in coconut and press 2/3 of mixture into bottom and up sides of well-greased (sprayed) 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Spread apples evenly; sprinkle evenly with blended sugar and cinnamon.
Blend sour cream and egg, then pour over apples.
Sprinkle remaining crust over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Cool gelatin and water.
Add nuts, cranberry sauce, pineapple and juice, wine and celery.
Let set.

title: chicken breasts with sour cream
directions: Mix spices and herbs together.
Dust chicken breasts in spice mixture and dredge with flour.
Heat butter in saute pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 minutes.
Season with salt. Turn pieces over and cook 3 minutes.
Add green onions to pan and cook 1 minute.
Pour in chicken stock and cook 6 minutes over low heat.
Do not cover.

title: sugar
directions: Mix these 2 ingredients, store in tightly closed container. This is so nice when served with tea or used in place of plain sugar in dessert recipes.
Sprinkle pancakes or waffles with this sugar and quickly caramelize under broiler before serving.
Stores for months!

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 inch x 13 inch pan with whole graham crackers to form a crust.
In bowl mix pudding mix and milk together.
Add Cool Whip and mix until blended.
Spread filling over graham crackers.
Top with a layer of graham crackers.
Chill overnight.	Frost with chocolate icing.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water for 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add sauce, salt and pepper to ground beef.
Put half of noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of the sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Heat oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling and pour over flour/sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add milk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows and mix well.
This will be a thin batter with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in flat pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.
(May use oblong or round layer cake pans.)

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until fully cooked. Let cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix in cream of chicken soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Put in casserole dish that has been greased with butter.

title: creamy chocolate cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into greased round or square pan.

title: potato cakes
directions: Using leftover mashed potatoes, add egg and green onion tops. Mix well.
Shape into biscuit-sized cakes, roll in flour and fry to golden brown in bacon drippings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans or 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Cream eggs, shortening and sugar.
Mix in pumpkin and water.
Blend in spices and dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins and put in pans.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes until clean.

title: peanut butter fudge balls or logs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
When it is mixed, shape it into small balls or roll into logs.

title: spinach with sesame seed
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add sesame seed.
Brown lightly and set aside.
Wash and drain spinach.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes and drain.
Reduce heat and reheat soy sauce and sesame seed.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all ingredients in a non-metal bowl.
Place in refrigerator for about 2 hours to allow flavors to mix.
Serve chilled.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients together to form a dip.
Cut a well in the middle of the loaf of bread.
Pour the dip into the well. Arrange bread pieces around the loaf.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine strawberry jam and sour cream and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add walnuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: french toast bundt
directions: Cut Rolls into fourths.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl.
Dip rolls in mixture and place in bundt pan sprayed with non-stick spray.
Pour remaining mixture over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise at room temperature until rolls reach the top of the pan.
Remove wrap and bake at 350 for 35 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter.
Drizzle with Syrup and sprinkle with Powdered Sugar.
Slice and serve with additonal Syrup.

title: chicken and english pea bake
directions: Combine
first	4
ingredients	in
a
shallow	2 quart casserole
dish.
Place
chicken breasts in casserole, turning to coat.
Add mushrooms; pour broth around chicken.
Cover and bake at	350°
for
50 minutes.	Add peas.
Cover and bake an additional 10 minutes, or until peas are tender.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, salt and celery.
When chicken is done, cool and remove from bone.
Make pie crust for top and bottom of pan.

title: baked acorn squash with crisp onions
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With large chef's knife, quarter squash lengthwise.
With spoon, scoop out and discard seeds.
Halve squash into pieces, lengthwise.
Place, skin side down, in jelly roll pan.
In small bowl, combine butter, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
With pastry brush, spread mixture evenly over inside of squash.
Sprinkle with almond slices and bake 45 minutes, until tender when tested with tip of paring knife.
In large skillet, saute onions.
Spread onions on squash.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper; dredge in cornmeal.
Heat bacon drippings in a heavy skillet; add tomatoes and fry slowly until browned, turning once. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 18 x 12-inch rectangle on sheet of wax paper.
Layer red pepper, onion and cheese on meat mixture, leaving 1-inch around edges.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Use wax paper to lift and roll.
Pinch edges and ends to seal.
Place loaf, seam side down, on rack of lightly greased broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix by hand to avoid breaking up cherries.
Bake in greased 10 x 15 jelly-roll pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave onion and pepper for 1 to 2 minutes, until tender. Mix all ingredients.
Spray 1-quart casserole with Pam.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla wafer crumb cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, beating well. Add crumbs and milk alternately. Add coconut and nuts. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool before removing from pan.

title: butterscotch-chocolate ice cream squares
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir while still warm to crumble.
Cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let stand 1/2 hour. Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
When jello begins to thicken, add cranberries, oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce and top with whipped cream.

title: coconut apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apple slices in shallow 1-quart dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Cream butter and 1/3 cup sugar; add egg, vanilla and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in flour gently.
Spread batter evenly over apple mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until crust top is crisp and golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tim's cornbread
directions: Mix everything and pour mixture into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: decorative icing
directions: Beat
sugar, meringue powder and 6 tbsp water in a mixer at medium speed, until smooth. Increase speed to highest and beat
5 minutes until thick and smooth, adding up to 1 tbsp. more water for piping consistency if necessary.

title: amish stewing noodles
directions: Make a soft dough by combining all ingredients (add more milk if necessary).
Turn dough onto a floured surface and knead until well worked.
Roll dough out as thin as possible and cut into strips about 1/2-inch wide and 2 inches long.
Let dry about 1 hour.
These noodles are great in soups and stews or great as dumplings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Do not salt!
Remove from bone and cut up; save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In a greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch), put a layer of dressing crumbs, a layer of chicken and the mushroom soup which has been diluted with one can of broth.
Again a layer of crumbs, a layer of chicken and the can of celery soup which has been diluted with a can of broth. Top with crumbs and bake at 350° until brown.

title: granny's date nut roll
directions: In saucepan, stir sugar, milk, syrup, margarine and dates. Cook to soft ball stage (240°).
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes firm.
Pour onto damp clean towel and shape into 1 1/2-inches thick roll.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice. This roll keeps for a long time in a tightly covered container.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients except apples and nuts.
Then add apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine apple juice, orange slices, cloves and 4 cinnamon sticks in medium saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and discard oranges, cloves and cinnamon sticks. Stir in Equal.
Pour into mugs.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks, if desired.
Makes 8 servings (4 ounces each).

title: hungry jack biscuit barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Cook 1 minute to blend flavor, stirring constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup.
Firmly press in bottom and up sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup of meat mixture into each biscuit lined cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt, mixing well.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles
coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture,
stirring	until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough
out onto a lightly floured surface.	Knead 8 to 10 times. Roll
dough to 1 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes until brown.

title: filled coffee cake
directions: Fill biscuits with the cream cheese and sugar to taste.
Seal edges with fingers.
Dip in melted butter or oleo.
Roll in a mixture of 1 cup sugar, orange rind and chopped nuts.
Stand up in Bundt pan (fills pan exactly).
Pour remainder of sugar-orange-nut mixture over biscuits (and butter).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 1 minute.
Turn out on plate.
Serve hot. Delicious!

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, chopped nuts and margarine; spread onto bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan (about 3 to 4 inches deep).
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Combine
sugar,
cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan. Bring to	a
boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from
heat and
add
oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined tray.
Let stand until cool.
Yields 32 servings.

title: devilish eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash yolks, then stir in mayonnaise, yogurt and Parmesan cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, if desired.
Fill the egg halves with the yolk mixture.

title: mushroom wine sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; set aside.

title: fudge candy
directions: Pour milk, sugar and margarine in saucepan and bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 9 minutes.
Place marshmallow, chocolate, nuts and vanilla in large bowl.
Add first set of mixture and blend well.
Pour in greased baking dish (glass) and let cool. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: I use 1/2 this recipe for my family of 4.

title: creamy chicken and bows
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and stir in chicken with red pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Add peas, cheese, garlic powder and Cup-a-Soup blended with milk.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes; toss with hot bows!
Makes 2 servings.

title: carrot and cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add vinegar and salt. Chill. When slightly thickened, fold in carrots and cabbage. Turn into individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce. Serve with mayonnaise.

title: oyster puffs
directions: Combine ingredients to make a stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chow-chow
directions: Mix all together; boil 20 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt a small amount of butter.
Add livers. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until livers are no longer pink.
Put livers through meat grinder.
Blend with mayonnaise, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons butter, onion, hot pepper sauce and seasonings.
Place mixture in 2-cup mold.
Chill several hours; carefully unmold.
Garnish with chopped, hard-cooked egg, chopped chives or snipped parsley.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and simmer for a few minutes. Next, add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into small pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together, drop pieces in and shake to coat.
Mix remaining mixture with butter.
Place coated pieces into greased tube or Bundt pan, pour remaining mixture over pieces.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes and serve warm.

title: super bean salad bowl
directions: Soak beans overnight in 6 cups water to which 2 teaspoons salt has been added.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Break egg into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, cinnamon, milk and lemon juice; beat until creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder into another bowl; add to mixture.
Mix well with spoon.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto 2 cookie sheets.
Do not grease them.
Leave one inch of space between cookies.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove from sheets; place on wire racks to cool.
Makes 36.

title: pimento sandwiches
directions: Mash pimentos and add cheese, salad dressing, vinegar, salt, pepper and then pickles if pickles are desired.
This makes about 15 sandwiches.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put marshmallow cream and peanut butter in bowl.
Boil milk and sugar to 238°.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Put in buttered pan.
After it starts setting, cut into squares.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients
together
and	pour into freezer.
Add enough homogenized milk to make a gallon.

title: glazed parsnips and carrots
directions: Cut carrots and parsnips into chunky diagonal slices.
In large skillet, cook carrots in boiling water until tender.
Drain. Cook parsnips the same way and drain.
In skillet, melt butter, stir in sugar.
Combine cornstarch and grapefruit juice. Stir into butter mixture.
Return vegetables to pan, keeping them separated.
Cook until glazed and heated through.
Kitchen tested and makes 8 servings.

title: "easy does it" breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
When brown, leave grease and sausage in skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until flour is blended with sausage.
Then add milk.
Cook until the gravy is the consistency that you like.
Serve over biscuits or bread.

title: shrimp skewers
directions: Alternate shrimp, vegetables and pineapple on 3 skewers. Broil or grill approximately 5 minutes on each side or until done. Baste with Italian dressing while cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done (you may need to add more liquid, tomato juice or water).
Add whatever vegetables you like.
Quick and easy, ready within an hour.

title: potato pinwheels
directions: Boil potato until done (no salt).
Let cool enough to handle, then peel.
While still hot, mash thoroughly.
Begin adding powdered sugar in small amounts at a time until the potato and powdered sugar mixture is at a rolled dough stage.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill for 5 to 6 hours.
Slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve cold.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except Snicker bars.
Wrap dough around candy bars and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: delicious deep-fried catfish
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dip fillets into milk, then dredge in flour mixture.
Pour corn oil in a heavy, 3-quart saucepan, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat to 375°.
Fry fillets 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve with hush puppies and cole slaw.

title: strawberry banana cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover tightly; blend until smooth and serve immediately.
Yield 3 to 4 servings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Place brown sugar, oleo and granulated sugar in saucepan.
Mix well and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over popcorn.
Toss and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour in peanuts, if wanted.

title: blinchiki
directions: Place butter in pan to heat; take off stove.
Add beaten eggs; add flour and salt.
Slowly add milk.
Fry each in hot buttered pan on both sides; fill and roll.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream until fluffy, one cup of sugar and 1/2 cup oleo.
Sift 2 cups of flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with egg and milk.
Beat well.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Put one cup boiling water in jello; let cool. Cream sugar and cheese together.
Whip milk until thick.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Add jello and lemon juice.
Fold into milk.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine; press into 11 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Add some cracker crumbs over the top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cold asparagus with lemon-mustard dressing
directions: Steam asparagus until crisp-tender and bright green; immediately drain and rinse under cold water.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice in small bowl; blend well.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon lemon peel; set aside.
Divide asparagus between plates.
Spoon 2 tablespoons dressing over top of each serving.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon lemon peel.
Garnish with carrot strips, if desired. Makes two appetizer servings.

title: brownies(triple recipe)
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add butter and cream together.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and chopped nuts.
Put in cookie sheet size pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole for four persons
directions: Mix flour and seasonings and dip chicken joints in this, coating well.
Remove rind and dice bacon.
Peel and slice onion. Wash and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter (or margarine) and oil in a frying pan, and fry chicken until golden brown.
Put into a casserole.
Lightly fry the bacon and onion; add to the chicken. Add the mushrooms and herbs.
Sprinkle in the rest of the flour. Pour off any fat left in the frying pan.
Add the hot water and stir to dissolve the sediment.
Add the chicken stock cubes and stir until dissolved.
Pour into the casserole.
Cover and cook until the chicken is tender (approximately 1 1/4 hours) at gas mark 4 (350°).

title: matzo meal pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, add water, salt and matzo meal; stir.
Melt a little butter in a pan and pour batter to form circles.
Turn when golden brown and cook until done.
Eat with jam or sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: david's chili
directions: Dice and fry the bacon.
Save the grease.
Saute the onions or fresh garlic in the bacon grease.
Brown the meat in small portions in the bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients except the cheese and Maza flour.
The water and beer should be added in equal amounts until a sufficient liquid level is obtained.
Bring the chili to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add the chicken mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Crush pretzels, then add sugar and oleo; mix well. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Save 1/2 cup of pretzel for topping.

title: lasagna no. 2
directions: Cook noodles and drain; set aside to cool.
Brown meat and onion.
Add all ingredients except noodles, cheeses and meat. Simmer sauce on low for 15 minutes.
Slice cheeses.
Spread a little sauce on bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Layer noodles, cheeses and sauce, ending with sauce and cheese on top. Bake at 325° until cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix with fork the flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add water, egg and vinegar.
Mix well, then with hands, mix into balls. Makes 3 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Chill dough before rolling out.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla; blend well and shape into 1-inch balls.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: *Thighs and breasts work great.

title: french chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg whites;
beat 1 minute.
Combine water, sour cream and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.
(With electric mixer use low speed.)
Pour into well greased and lightly floured (2) 8 in round pans at least 1 1/2 in deep.
Bake in 350 degree oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: In
a bowl, stir together the 1 cup of cornmeal, baking soda and salt;
stir in milk, eggs and corn.
Stir in cheese, chili peppers and onion;	mix until well blended.
Meanwhile, in	a large
skillet,
cook
ground beef until brown.
Drain. Stir
in beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder. Cook
until heated through.
Grease and sprinkle a thin layer of cornmeal over
the
bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Turn
1/2 of the cornmeal batter into the dish.
Cover with	the
meat-bean mixture
and top with remaining cornmeal mixture.	Bake
at
350° for
hour
or until top is golden brown.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add cabbage, carrots and onion; toss to mix well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 6 servings.

title: daisy's blueberry cake(makes 16 servings)
directions: In a bowl, mix together the butter and sugar until creamy. Stir in vanilla and orange rind.
Beat in the egg.
Stir in orange juice.
Mixture will be slightly curdled.

title: blueberry cake
directions: In a large measuring cup put oil and 2 eggs; fill up cup with milk to make 2 cups total liquid.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients (flour pint of blueberries); fold into batter.
Pour into a large greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Umm good!

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix well and pour into a well-greased baking dish.
To double recipe, use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° if using a glass dish or 350° for other kind of dish. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
I prefer to use fresh corn.
Add a little milk, salt and pepper.
Cook for a few minutes and cool. Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; add salt and pepper to your taste.
Cover meat with sauce and soak in refrigerator overnight.
Turn meat occasionally while soaking.

title: onion and bacon quiche
directions: Cook onions in butter (15 to 20 minutes) until soft.
While onions cook, saute bacon until lightly browned.
Drain well.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: Mix
egg, water and vinegar together.
Combine salt and flour. Pour
egg
mixture into the center of the dry ingredients.
Stir with
a
fork
from
the middle to the outer edge until
mixed. Chill.
Roll
out and place in pie pans.
Makes enough dough for 5 pies.

title: cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F. Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour cherry pie filling in baking pan, spread evenly, pour 1/2 cake mix over filling, do not stir. Add pecans and coconut.
Add the other half of the cake mix over pecans and coconut, pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350 F for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet `n' sour slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seeds to boil. Allow to cool and pour over cabbage, pepper and celery. Better if allowed to set overnight. Will keep several days.

title: veal scallopini piccata
directions: Dredge veal medallions in flour; shake well.
Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Cook veal on both sides until browned.
Cut 2 lemons and squeeze over veal.
Season to taste.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Serve on platter; garnish with the third lemon, sliced thin.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except raisins.
In an 11 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle bottom evenly with the 3/4 cup raisins. Pour the ingredients over raisins.
Place pan inside larger pan filled with 1 inch water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Pudding will "set" after removal from oven.
Don't overbake.

title: corn fritters
directions: In electric skillet, heat 1/2-inch oil to 400°.
In medium bowl with fork stir one tablespoon oil and rest of the ingredients until blended.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoons into hot oil. Fry 3 to 5 minutes until browned, turning once.
With slotted spoon remove fritters to paper towels.
Drain.
Serve with syrup or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soups, broth and Veg-All. Pour over chicken. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tasty vegetable casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions in butter until soft and golden brown.
Add beef and toss with a fork until red color disappears.
Add salt, pepper, and rice.
Mix well.
Stir in peas, tomatoes, and cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: creamsicle punch
directions: Soften ice cream and sherbet with wire whisk.
Blend in milk. Add juice and ginger ale.
Makes about 50 (5 ounce) servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Our sixth generation of cooks has already started thinking of cooking.
Carole Underwood's four year old granddaughter asked her to make some Blueberry Muffins.
Carole asked her granddaughter, Morgan, if she knew how and she replied, "Yes, me and mommie make them all the time; you take 4 pounds of water and mix it with 3 eggs and a box of sugar and cook it.
That's all you do."
Now how about that for a 4 year old?

title: jan's baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion together.
Mix with the rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 400° oven until it bubbles, then bake at 325° until thick and liquid has cooked down.
This will take at least 1 hour.
Taste to see if mixture is sweet before baking. Also, it should have a dark red color.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Squeeze grated potatoes with your hands to remove as much liquid as possible.
Stir remaining ingredients into drained potatoes.
Heat oil (enough for 1/2-inch depth) in a frying pan. Spoon potato mixture by large tablespoons into oil and flatten each pancake with back of spatula.
Fry until golden, then turn and fry on other side.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot, with applesauce or sour cream.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and soda in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: swiss onion tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Over medium heat, saute onions in butter, slowly, until they are translucent and soft.
Sprinkle flour over them, mix well and let cook a couple of minutes. Remove from heat and add egg yolks.
Gradually stir in cream.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, mayonnaise, cheese and onions.
Put in buttered baked dish, 9 x 8-inches or 12 x 8-inches.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Don't peel the potatoes; cook them whole and let cool.
Substituting for Velveeta cheese is not recommended.

title: drunk hot dogs
directions: Mix all together; cook.
Add water or whiskey as needed.
Keep warm in crock-pot or skillet while serving.

title: sour cream dressing(for cole slaw or cucumber and onions)
directions: Beat ingredients; pour over cabbage, shredded thin, or cucumber and onions.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to
Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Cut in shortening until like
coarse crumbs.
Make a well; add milk all at once.
Stir
quickly
with a fork just until dough follows fork around
bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured surface. Knead gently 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll out dough 1/2 inch thick. Dip
cutter into flour;
cut
dough
straight
down.
Bake
on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mike's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Add spaghetti sauce and crushed tomatoes to a 5-quart saucepan and heat.
Brown chopped meat in a skillet and drain.
Saute chopped onions and chopped green peppers in heated corn oil.
Add chopped meat, onions, green peppers, basil, Italian seasoning, crushed red peppers, bay leaves, garlic powder, salt and sugar to sauce and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: fig preserves
directions: Cook in a large pot over very low heat until syrup is thickened.
To check syrup, dip spoon in syrup and let cool. Syrup should be thick enough not to pour off.

title: chicken pie
directions: Line bottom of pie pan with crescent pie crust.
Mix chicken, soup and peas and carrots.	Pour into pie crust.
Top with another crescent pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger rice soup
directions: Mix and brown ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and onion in a large saucepan.
Add tomato juice and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add rice, turn off heat, cover and let stand 15 minutes.
If soup becomes too thick, you can add water or more tomato liquid.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and vanilla. Add 2 beaten egg yolks, sour cream and raisins. Stir well and cook over medium heat until thickened. Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Top with 2 egg whites (beaten until stiff). Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; build up slight edge.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Have apples ready, mixed with sugar and cinnamon (blend to create juice).
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Blend sour cream and egg; drizzle over apples to cover.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients in double plastic food bag. Shake well.
Prepare a 10 x 15 x 3/4-inch pan with Pam or wipe it well with oil.
Run a cut-up fryer chicken under cold water and let excess water drip or put the wet chicken pieces into a colander and drain a few minutes.
Dredge pieces in the flour mixture by placing each piece, one at a time, into the bag of seasoned flour and shaking it.
Arrange the coated pieces, skin side up, on the prepared pan.
Melt 1/4 pound butter or margarine and, using a soft bristled brush, dab the melted margarine over the floured surface skin side only, of each piece.
When all of the melted margarine has been divided among all the chicken pieces, bake them, uncovered, without turning at 375° for 20 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.

title: dorothy's meat loaf
directions: Form the meat then mix 1 can stewed tomatoes and 1 can tomato paste. Pour on top of meat. Bake at 350 degrees until brown on top.

title: cheese bread
