directions: Measure Bisquick in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until center tests done.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt with apples and set aside. Combine shortening, flour and salt in a bowl.
Add enough to egg yolks to make 2/3 cup of liquid and add to pie crust mixture. Divide dough in half.
Use a 17 x 11-inch cookie sheet and place 1/2 of dough on cookie sheet.
Press with hand or roll with rolling pin until bottom and sides are covered.
Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on dough.
Add apple mixture.
Roll other half of dough to fit the top.
Press around edge with thumb.
Beat egg whites stiff, spread over top of dough.
(Do not add sugar to egg whites.) Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cover with thin powdered sugar frosting while warm.
Makes 18 servings.

title: dough for christmas ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Gradually add water, a little at a time.
Knead until dough is smooth and putty like.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° until light brown or let dry on screen for 48 hours.

title: coconut-chocolate treats
directions: Melt margarine; stir in sugar and coconut.
Chill.
Shape rounded teaspoons of mixture into balls.
Flatten slightly. Indent center of each.
Fill with melted chocolate.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: recipe of mother's love
directions: Throw in a little hope, dreams, hugs and kisses.
Mix well. Use daily.
Don't let temperature get over 300°.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop into hot broth, dipping spoon in hot broth each time.

title: pineapple surprise sheet cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Remove from oven. Spread crushed pineapple (juice and all) over cake.
Mix pudding mix with milk and cream cheese.
Spread over the pineapple and spread with Cool Whip.
Top off cake with coconut.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple, sugar and water to boil.
Dissolve jello into the hot mixture.
Cool in refrigerator until it is the consistency of egg whites.
Add cheese and nuts.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl or mold; refrigerate until set.

title: tomato-vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a large Dutch oven; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.	Yield:	about 5 quarts. Great served with corn bread.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and almond flavorings.
Pour mixture in tube pan that has been thoroughly greased.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add onions, garlic and salt.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and heat to a boil.

title: denver omelet pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs, onion powder, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir in the potatoes, cheese, ham and green pepper.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Garnish with tomato slices.
Serves 6.

title: rich scones
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Rub in Crisco or margarine. Mix in fruit and sugar.
Stir in beaten egg and milk. Make into soft dough.

Roll out to thickness of 1/2-inch and cut in rounds with a 2 1/2-inch scone cutter. Place on greased baking sheet. Brush over tops with tablespoon of beaten egg. Bake in a 425° to 450° oven for about 10 minutes, gas oven 7 to 8 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stem end off pepper.
Remove seed.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover 5 minutes.
Cook hamburger and onion in skillet until light brown.
Stir in salt, rice and 1 can tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
(Save 1 can to go on top of peppers.) Stuff pepper with hamburger mixture.
Stand upright in an ungreased baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; cook 15 minutes longer. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Melt butter in broth.
Add soup, then seasoned mix.
Add chicken and sour cream.
Add broth to chicken; mix if too thick. Butter baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything, except butter, together. Pour in large casserole dish. Cut butter into small chunks on top of mixture. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°. Do not cover.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients except Kisses and extra sugar.
Shape dough into balls, approximately 1 tsp.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375°
for 10 - 12 minutes.
When done quickly top each with a Kiss pressing firmly into cookie.

title: lo-cal dessert lime fluff
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add to cottage cheese mixture, then add marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Defrost Cool Whip.
Put in a large bowl. Add crushed pineapple with juice and stir. Add the pudding and stir.
Add the marshmallows. Stir and let sit in refrigerator until chilled (1 to 2 hours).
Great all year long, especially good in summer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Spoon out on cookie sheet and let cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into balls to freeze.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: fantastic mint chocolate pie
directions: Place margarine, corn syrup and chocolate in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add Cocoa Krispies cereal to chocolate mixture.
Stir until cereal is coated.
With back of spoon, shape mixture evenly in bottom and on side of 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
(If mixture is too soft, refrigerate about five minutes.)
Chill crust.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: angel pineapple pie
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and water to boiling point.
Add cornstarch that has been dissolved in a little water.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip and nuts.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Frost when fully cooled with cream cheese frosting.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well with mixer or blender.
Refrigerate.
Set out 30 minutes before serving to soften.

title: ginger, mint and lemon grass sun tea
directions: Fill a 1-gallon glass container with water.
Put all ingredients in water and leave in the sun for 1 to 2 days, depending on sunshine.

title: overnight black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight.
Can be served on salad greens or in a bowl with Fritos or other dippers for hors d'oeuvres.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Put in a greased casserole and top with crushed potato chips. Bake in a 450° oven until hot and brown on top.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine Karo, peanuts, water, sugar and salt.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 13 more minutes on High.
Test with candy thermometer.
If not to 300°, microwave on High for 60 seconds, then test again.
Keep testing after every minute until it reaches 300°.
Quickly stir in soda and vanilla until light and foamy.
Turn out onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: "youvarlakia" - meatball soup
directions: For broth, I often use bouillon cubes to make the broth.

title: oatmeal caramelitos
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, soda, salt and margarine. Press 1/2 of crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Take from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips (can add nuts also) over baked crust.
Combine caramel syrup and 6 tablespoons flour, mixing well, and drizzle over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over topping.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Chill bars.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in brownie pan.
Mix remainder in bowl; add oleo, then nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed wafers and melted butter; press into bottom of rectangle dish.
Slice bananas lengthwise and cover bottom.
Avoid overly ripe bananas.
Use yellow skinned or green tipped.
Mix together condensed milk and lemon juice; spread on top of bananas. Spread crushed pineapple on top of Eagle Brand layer.
Cover with whipped topping (8 to 9 ounce is plenty).
Sprinkle coconut, chopped nuts and arrange red cherries on top to designate serving size.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Easy, no cooking, pretty and good!

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix sugar, crumbs and melted oleo.
Line pan and sides.

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Beat together onion and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
This is a thick dressing.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
and flour large sheet cake baking pan.
Beat	sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large mixer bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 1 minute. Stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in cinnamon, nuts and raisins. Pour into pan and
bake approximately 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting
or
is
delicious
served with whipped cream.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° on a greased cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: canned corn
directions: Take 1 cup friendly words, 2 cups heaping of understanding and 4 heaping teaspoonful of time and patience.
Add a pinch of warm personality and a dash of humor.
Measure the words carefully and the heaping amounts of time and patience.
Keep temperature low; do not boil.
Add a dash of humor and a pinch of warm spice of life. Serve in individual molds and garnish with smiles.
This recipe never fails.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Brown mushrooms, beef and onion in shortening.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add mushroom liquid, water, 57 sauce and parsley; combine well.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve immediately over noodles.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Place the apples on squares of pastry rolled to about 6-inches.
Mix the water, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and margarine. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Pour over dumplins in pan and bake in oven at 375° until apples are done and dumplins are nicely brown. Dip sauce over them while baking.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Spray Dutch oven with nonstick coating.
Brown meat.
Stir in water, apple juice, undrained tomatoes, sauerkraut, onion, bouillon, pepper and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Stir in apple and simmer 5 minutes more.
Yields 5 servings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Put the egg in a cup.
Add fruit juice to measure a cup. Combine oats, baking powder and salt.
Combine honey, oil, juice, egg and dried fruit.
Mix together until blended.
Fill and slightly mound in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: head cheese
directions: Cook pork, veal, pork bones and onions in kettle with only 1 to 2-inches of water in bottom.
Cook at least 3 hours or until meat begins to fall off.
Cut meat from bones; save cooking water, at least 1 cup.
Mix all ingredients along with dissolved gelatin in a large bowl.
Pour into glass loaf pans and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Add onions and green pepper; cook until the onions are transparent.
Add the rice, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, seasonings and cabbage. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Great casserole to take to a potluck supper!

title: dream bars
directions: Thoroughly blend butter, sugar and cake flour; spread in lightly greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs and brown sugar until thick; add sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and coconut; spread over first mixture.
Continue baking 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and cool in pan.
Makes 2 dozen squares.

title: macaroni and cheese quiche
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package, except use 2 tablespoons milk instead of amount required.
Add 2 eggs; mix well.
Spread over bottom and sides of greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Toss Swiss cheese with flour; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over dinner mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil; continue baking 20 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans excellent
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Good with ham.

title: farm style cinnamon rolls
directions: Let dough thaw and rise almost double in size.
Brush 8 x 10-inch pan or 9 x 9-inch with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Roll out dough on floured surface.
Brush with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll up.
Cut with a knife into 12 pieces.
Place side up in buttered pan.
Brush with remaining butter.
Let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut soup
directions: Peel and grate the fresh coconuts.
In a saucepan, scald the milk and stir in grated coconut.
Let stand until cold and squeeze the juice through a napkin.
In a saucepan, add juice to the broth and bring to the boiling point.
Beat egg yolks in a tureen and pour the soup over.
Serve hot, decorated with toasted almonds. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and grated cheese.
Add red pepper and flour. Put in cookie press and make sticks, 2 1/3 to 3-inches long.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 100 sticks, 6-inches long.

title: entomatadas(mexican dish)
directions: In skillet brown ground meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and salt.
Remove from range.
Pour meat in flour tortillas; roll like burritos.
Place in a baking pan.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, pour tomato sauce, white onion and salt; cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Pour over burritos.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Soften cream cheese by adding sugar and mayo.
Add cranberries and pineapple; mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in loaf pan lined with plastic.
Put in freezer for 24 hours.
Take out and put on dish.
Apply extra Cool Whip as icing and re-freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Rinse chicken with cold water and pat dry.
Dip chicken in butter and dredge in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Slice potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with a layer of cheese.
Place pork chops on top of cheese and season.
(Optional:
Add another layer of cheese.) Spread cream of mushroom soup over top.
Cover and bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour, until potatoes and pork chops are done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Add sugar, flour, salt, peaches and brandy to margarine in saucepan.
Cook for about 4 minutes after it comes to a boil. Pour mixture into a greased casserole dish.

title: angel food pie
directions: Cook pineapple, juice, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in double boiler until very thick; stir constantly to prevent lumping. Remove from heat and cool.
Beat egg whites to a soft peak, adding 4 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Fold into cooled filling gently. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese,
margarine,	milk
and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in powdered sugar until smooth.

title: heath bar crunch ice cream
directions: Freeze the candy bars.
Beat the eggs by hand until fluffy. Slowly add sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into an ice cream maker and freeze.
(Follow maker's directions.) While ice cream is freezing, break candy bars into small pieces with a knife handle.
When ice cream is done, add candy pieces and mix well.
Store in freezer.
Makes 1 quart.

title: vanilla ice cream(for 1 gallon)
directions: Scald milk and 1 cup sugar, then mix 1 cup sugar, flour, salt and eggs with 2 cups cold milk.
Stir into boiling milk; stir until it boils again over low heat to prevent from sticking.
Add vanilla and cream; add enough milk to fill freezer can.
Very good and smooth ice cream.

title: vegetable casserole(very good!)
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt 1/3 cup oleo, then mix with crushed Ritz crackers and cover vegetables in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot wieners
directions: Slice wieners.
Set aside.
Mix cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce in crock-pot.
Let get hot.
Add wieners.
Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: On an 8-inch round tray, spread cream cheese, then spread seafood cocktail sauce.
Add cheese, shrimp, olives and tomato.

title: old fashion hermits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on 11 x 7-inch greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: butter and cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each one.
Alternately add the flour and whipping cream. Grease cake pan with Crisco.
Place in cold oven and cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: feather light sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon peel.
Beat until well mixed.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Wrap and chill for several hours.
Divide dough into thirds.
Refrigerate portions until ready to use.
Form cookie by rolling teaspoon of dough into balls.
Flatten with a glass that has been set in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let set for 2 minutes before removing to cool. Makes 7 dozen.

title: chandler's favorite peanut butter squares
directions: Stir together
peanut butter, 1/2 c. margarine and powdered sugar.
Mixture will be stiff.
Press into 9 inch square pan. Spread topping over top of peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate to set chocolate topping.
Cut into small squares.

title: delta dawn shrimp pasta
directions: Add garlic and sausage to a large saucepan and heat over a moderate flame.
Saute until the garlic is tender.
Drain any excess oil.
Add the butter.
When melted, add the parsley and green onions. Stir well and let the vegetables cook down, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the shrimp, sprinkle with lemon juice and blend well with the other ingredients in the saucepan.
Stir in the heavy cream and let the ingredients simmer for 5 minutes or until the shrimp are fully cooked and bright pink.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and pepper in vegetable oil.
When rice is golden brown, add water and tomato sauce.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low and cook slowly for 5 minutes while covered with lid.

title: hearty beef and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and seasonings.
Simmer while preparing crust.
Spread crescent roll dough in ungreased 9-inch pie pan and up the sides.

title: enchiladas
directions: Chop 1 onion, olives and grate cheese.
Set aside.
Fry beef, 3 onions and peppers together.
When onions are coked, drain and put into boiling pot with tomato juice, olive juice, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Boil until blended.
While this cooks, warm tortillas over low open fire.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease cake pin.
Combine all ingredients except nuts until creamy.
Sprinkle all the nuts on bottom of cake pan and add the mixture.
Bake for approximately 55 minutes.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
In saucepan, cook clams, garlic and parsley in margarine a few minutes.
Stir in soup, milk, clam liquid and cheese.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked pasta.

title: coconut cream pie filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix egg yolks with milk.
Combine and cook over low heat, stirring until thick enough.
Add coconut and vanilla.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into mixing bowl. Cut in the shortening.
Add enough milk to look like thick cake batter.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour undrained peaches or cherries on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over peaches or 1 cup sugar over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tasty cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine eggs, flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, baking powder and butter.
Pour into an ungreased 9 inch x 14 inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 12 - 15 minutes. Remove from oven and spread peanut butter evenly over cake.
Let set in refrigerator until cool.
Melt chocolate bars and spread evenly over peanut butter.
Let set in refrigerator until firm. Cut into desired squares before hard.

title: peach cream cheese pie(makes 2 pies.)
directions: Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch, then add cold water. Cook until thick. Add 5 or 6 fresh sliced peaches. Refrigerate.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup
and	water
until it spins a thread. Beat egg whites until they are stiff.
Pour syrup mixture over egg whites, then
beat	until
foamy.
Add flavoring, nuts and coloring, if desired.
Pour in buttered plates.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350 for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chinese egg roll pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs and water in bowl.
Sift in the flour and salt; beat until smooth with a rotary beater.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber and onion slices in a large bowl. Layer with salt and cover with ice cubes. Let stand 1 1/2 hours; drain and rinse. Place remaining ingredients in large sauce pot and bring to a boil. Add drained cucumbers and onions and return to a boil. Pack hot in hot jars. Remove air bubbles. Adjust caps. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes about 7 pints.

title: lola faye's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, shortening and eggs together.
Mix baking soda with flour.
Gradually blend in flour mixture and milk.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.	Mix flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg. Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat until well blended.
Add pumpkin; blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 55 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: budget beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup mix, wine, soup and beef in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake covered 1 hour.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: banana-fudge brownies a la mode
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions, reducing water to 2 tablespoons and using only one egg white; stir mashed banana into batter.
Bake in an 8-inch square baking pan for 25 minutes; cool as directed.
Cut cooled brownies into 9 squares.
Serve each brownie topped with 1/4 cup scoop of frozen yogurt and 1 teaspoon of chocolate syrup.

title: you're lucky if you get some
directions: Combine ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken wings and curried rice
directions: Cut wings at both joints.
Make stock from wing tips.
Beat egg, oil and water together.
Dip wing pieces in and place on rack. Sprinkle with cornstarch on both sides; salt lightly and brown in hot oil.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Make sauce of catsup, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar and stock.
Pour over wings and cover. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Saute onions, pepper and celery until crisp (in oil left from browning wings).
Stir in curry powder and rice.
Serve barbecue wings over curried rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef;
drain
fat.
Combine
with
soup, water, onion and mixed vegetables.
Mix well.
Bake in covered dish
45 minutes at 350°.
After baking, remove cover and add Tater Tots to top and bake 15 minutes longer at 400°.

title: potato salad recipe
directions: Mix all of these together, except potatoes.
Cook potatoes with jackets on; cool and dice.
Add after everything has been mixed together.
For top, save 2 eggs.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons paprika and 2 tablespoons salad seasoning.

title: brownie chip cookies
directions: Combine brownie mix, eggs and oil; beat about 50 strokes with a spoon.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool about 2 minutes on cookie sheets.
Remove to wire racks and let cool completely.
Yield 5 to 6 dozen.

title: diet dreamsicle
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add ice cubes to make 2 cups.
Let stand 5 minutes.
With mixer, add vanilla pudding, then add drained oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze in containers.

title: red and green holiday salad
directions: Line salad bowl with lettuce.
Arrange broccoli and tomatoes on top.
Combine oil, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Mix well; pour over salad.
Sprinkle with croutons.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Line bottom of crust with sliced bananas.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix milk with pudding; add cream cheese.
Beat until thick.
Put in crust; chill for 2 hours.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Chill about an hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 375° hot oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely.
Remove from sheets to cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add eggs, shortening, milk and rhubarb.
Pour into 9 X 13 pan.
Mix the brown sugar and chopped walnuts; sprinkle over top and bake in 375° oven for about 40 minutes, or until done.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Add flavor packets from noodles; mix well.
Add vegetables and stir.
Add crushed noodles and stir. Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Stir 3 or 4 times in between the 24 hours.
For a big bowl, double this recipe.

title: broccoli-sausage quiche
directions: Line unbaked pie shell with double thickness of foil. Bake in a 450° oven for 8 minutes. Remove foil. Bake for 4 to 6 minutes more or until golden. Remove from oven.
Set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.

title: mushroom parmesan
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add mushrooms.
Cook over low heat, covered, until wilted.
In saucepan, blend 3 tablespoons of butter with flour and add milk, sour cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg and stir until thickened.
Pour mushrooms into casserole.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot; serve.

title: best ever green beans
directions: In large skillet, melt bacon grease on high.
Pan must be hot. Add green beans and allow to sizzle for a minute or two.
Add sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Allow them to sizzle on medium-high for about 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Beans will cook down quite a bit.
We've tried this recipe with other green beans, but none work like Double Luck.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: In a skillet, combine candies and sugar; add water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until liquid boils.
Add apple rings to candy mixture.
Simmer gently, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir and spoon candy mixture over apples.
Cool apple rings in candy mixture.
Drain.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into an ungreased 8-inch square pan. Make three little "wells" in dry ingredients.
Pour salad oil in one, vinegar in the second and vanilla in the third.
Add milk and stir with a fork until mixture is well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and blend at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill pans half full.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on platter.
Spread taco sauce over this.
Layer pepper, tomato and onion.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolk.
Add flour. Roll dough into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Press with back of floured fork in one direction to flatten.
Top each with pecan pieces.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned around edges.
Remove from pan while still warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in chicken, carrots, celery and peas; reserve.
Prepare Celery Seed Pastry.

title: "cold oven" butternut flavoring cake
directions: Cream the shortening, margarine, sugar and salt well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in nuts and cherries by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 3/4 hours at 325°.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open oven door while baking. Remove from pan immediately.
Invert on wire rack to cool.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together oleo, eggs and sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk (sour milk:
2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vinegar). Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt and apples.
Top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: lobster in chafing dish
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in pan; saute lobster and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle in flour and stir.
Add cream and shrimp. Season with salt, pepper, nutmeg, sherry and cheese.
Add egg yolks slowly.
Place in chafing dish and allow to thicken.
If necessary, can be thinned with cream.
Serve on Melba toast rounds.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place 2 teaspoons in cup or mug, or to taste; add boiling water.

title: cucumber rounds
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, dry Italian dressing mix and mayonnaise until smooth.
Cover bread rounds with mixture.
Place a cucumber slice on top of each bread round.
Sprinkle dill seed over the cucumber slices.
Makes 5 to 7 dozen.

title: microwave caramel apples
directions: You will need wooden sticks.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serves 8.

title: love-drop cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with red sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: "rocks" (grandma helen's christmas cookies)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cream
of tartar.
Add to mixture.
Slightly flour fruit and add.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until done (about 8 minutes).

title: tomato-feta salad
directions: Rub inside of salad bowl with garlic; discard garlic.
Combine tomatoes, olives and cheese in salad bowl.
Combine oil and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over tomato mixture, tossing gently. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream cheese with shrimp and guacamole dip
directions: Cream together cheese, mayo, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Spread mixture on a rimmed plate.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, cover chilled cheese with avocado dip, then with a layer of picante sauce.
Then top with the shrimp.
Sprinkle with the green onions and serve with tortilla chips.
Scoop through all layers to eat.

title: pumpkin bread(fall bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two loaf pans.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil, orange juice and pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients. Blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased pans. Bake 1 hour.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Mash cheese and Crisco; cream well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Roll into small balls; chill 1 hour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Balls will flatten as they cook.
Serve at your next brunch.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter on High (10) for 1/2 minute or until melted. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on High (10) for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes and each minute until thick and bubbly.
Layer half of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Cover. Microwave on High (10) for 22 to 26 minutes.
Chunks or slices of ham may be added.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk yeast buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add buttermilk and sugar.
Let mixture stand 15 minutes.
Add butter and eggs; mix.
Sift soda and salt with 4 cups flour and add to liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth batter forms.
Add remaining sifted flour, stirring with spoon until thick enough to handle with hands.
Knead on floured board.
Place in large greased mixing bowl.
Turn.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; form into buns.
(Squeeze dough into balls the size of an egg.)
Place on greased baking sheet; flatten slightly with hand.
Let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 48 buns.

title: macaroni ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Place in large mixing bowl and stir other ingredients. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Top with crushed potato chips or cracker crumbs drizzled with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Make 3 wells in mixture.
Pour vinegar in first well, vanilla in second and oil in the third.
Cover with 2 cups cold water, mixing with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear pie
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, flour and egg.
Spoon mixture over prepared pears.
The mixture is a little stiff.
Place it as biscuits over the pears.
When baked it runs together and makes a good crust.

title: fish casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and cracker crumbs, butter or oleo and paprika. Cook rice and celery together. Bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press onto dough.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cookies do not brown. Sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: vitality bread
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients.
Put on low heat until almost boiling; it will get real thick.
Add 1 cup warm water and 1/2 cup flour; let cool to lukewarm.
Add this mixture that has been sitting, the yeast and 1/2 cup warm water.
Add the remaining flour.
Knead on oiled board until glossy.
Place in oiled bowl; cover.
Set in warm place until double in size.
Punch and knead; put into 3 greased pans.
Let double.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple-carrot salad(may be served to toddlers or nineties)
directions: Shred apples and carrot on finest shredder.
Add raisins and just enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Serve on a Boston leaf lettuce.
Makes 3 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Add chopped onion and cook.
Add remainder of ingredients, mix together and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and flour.
Add everything else but eggs.
Stir with spoon until well mixed.
Pour into a greased pan or dish.
Add eggs and mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: bean fondue dip
directions: Keep in reserve 1 cup cheese.
Mix rest of cheese and all other ingredients.
Spread in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Wrap and refrigerate at this point if making ahead.
If not, bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips for dipping.
Serves 18.

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine the first seven ingredients.
Crumble meat over top; mix well.
Shape into loaf; place in greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Mix catsup and BBQ sauce.
Pour over top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: deep-fried okra
directions: Wash okra; drain.
Cut off tips and stem ends.
Cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine flour, cracker meal, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper in a shallow dish.

Combine egg, buttermilk and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt in a dish, mixing well. Add about 1/3 of okra to egg mixture, then remove okra with a slotted spoon and place in flour mixture, stirring gently, to coat okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2-inches into a Dutch oven and heat to 375°.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Continue process with remaining okra.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook pasta shells as directed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg (will be a paste). Add milk; cook on low until thick.
Add spinach to sauce.
Put in baking dish.
Mix tuna and Ricotta cheese.
Fill shells with mixture.
Arrange shells on top of spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.

title: yams souffle
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 1-quart souffle dish.
Place the yams in a large pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender, 20 to 30 minutes, drain and set aside to cool.
Peel the yams.
In a bowl, mash the yams.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar, the egg yolks, 2 tablespoons butter, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and milk; beat well.
Whisk egg whites until peaks form.
Fold into mixture.
Pour the yam mixture into the prepared souffle dish.
Dot the top with the remaining butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix at low speed.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
This will also make 8 mini loaf pans. Bake mini loaf pans about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
When cool, ice with sour cream icing.

title: speedy rolls(makes 36)
directions: Place water, sugar and yeast in bowl to dissolve.
Add salt and 2 cups of flour.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add egg and melted shortening.
Beat for 1 minute.
Gradually add 4 1/2 cups flour, stirring until dough is formed.
Allow dough to rest for 20 minutes, for each of handling.

title: helen's easy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, slice bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice to keep them from turning dark.
Open all fruit; drain and save juice for a fruit punch.
Mix all fruits; pour pie filling in and mix well.
Can decorate with some strawberries and kiwi.

title: leftover turkey loaf
directions: Place butter in small dish and cook 1/2 minute or until melted.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, bread crumbs, pimento, green peppers, parsley and turkey.
Add butter and mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart ovenware dish.
Cover.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Layer croutons, cheese and sausage.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Top with soup diluted with milk.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and saute onion.
Add sauce.
Combine beef mixture and cooked noodles.
In a large casserole dish, layer beef noodle mixture, cheese and pepperoni until all is used.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: polish sausage, cabbage and potato meal
directions: In hot oil in large, heavy skillet over medium heat lightly brown sliced kielbasa.
Remove from pan, set aside.
To remaining fat in skillet add cabbage, potatoes and onion.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Sprinkle vegetables with flour, mix well.
Add water to chicken broth to make 1 1/2 cups.
Return sausage to skillet.
Add broth, vinegar, caraway, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown
beef, onion and green pepper (drain the grease); add tomatoes
and corn.
Simmer until thick; add chili powder and season
to	taste.	Add noodles; put in greased casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic in skillet, stirring frequently; drain.
Layer ground beef mixture, rice and cabbage 1/2 at a time in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour juice over all.
Bake, covered, with foil at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
